nce litigation action has been instigated you will be liable to discharge all Legal fees whether we are successful or not. In the instance recovery is obtained from the debtor, the Legal fees recovered will duly be credited to you.</sub></p>\r\n<p><sub>** Alternative enforcement procedures are available and advice and costings can be supplied on request.</sub></p>','2010-11-12 17:13:46','2011-11-21 13:06:48','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Track the progress of your debt collections on line with our new Debt Interactive</p>\r\n<p>LOG IN HERE</p>','86_iStock_000008332115XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',52852,'2011-03-30 10:49:05','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DebtRecovery.jpg','image/jpeg',49439,'2010-12-22 09:24:14','Debt Recovery','','','Debt Recovery','','https://www.bannerjones-debtrecovery.co.uk',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(30,'Banner Jones Debt Interactive','banner_jones_debt_interactive','Banner Jones Debt Interactive',30,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','','2010-11-12 17:14:14','2011-03-03 16:11:32','','',1,2,1,'2011-03-03 16:11:32',1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(31,'Corporate Crime','corporate_crime','Corporate Crime',31,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>Are you under the spotlight?</h2>\r\n<p>This can be a very worrying time for the manager and staff of a business and we know you&rsquo;ll need a legal partner who has experience in this field and can guide you through it step by step.&nbsp; We deal with emergency situations on a daily basis and are experienced in defending companies being prosecuted for every type of offence. Whether the matter relates to your premises or the protection of staff or customers we can advise and defend you.</p>\r\n<p>Some of our areas of expertise include</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Health &amp; Safety breaches</li>\r\n<li>Trading Standards </li>\r\n<li>Environmental Law</li>\r\n<li>Fraud and Financial Crime Investigation</li>\r\n<li>Regulatory Offences</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Whatever the problem our lawyers will go through your case with you and give you an honest opinion of the likely outcome.</p>\r\n<p>When faced with serious business issues such as this, would it benefit you to know you could just pick up the phone to an experienced commercial lawyer without incurring an additional charge?&nbsp; With a fixed cost monthly retainer from <a href=\"../../../page/total-legal-care-insurance\">Total Legal Care</a>, we&rsquo;ll give you business and employment law advice whenever you need it at no additional cost.</p>','2010-11-12 17:14:38','2011-11-29 14:56:17','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Let us help you stay on the right side of the law for an affordable fixed monthly cost</p>','110_tlc.JPG','image/jpeg',18257,'2011-03-30 10:51:31','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','CorporateCrime.jpg','image/jpeg',45932,'2010-12-22 09:23:49','Corporate Crime','','','Corporate Crime','/page/total-legal-care-insurance','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(32,'Notary','notary_services','Notary in Chesterfield',32,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>We provide a fast and efficient Notary Public service in Chesterfield at competitive rates. Whether you are a business engaged in international trade or you wish to be married outside the UK, we provide a comprehensive, high quality service.</p>\r\n<h2>What is a Notary Public?</h2>\r\n<p>A Notary is a qualified lawyer with a specialist additional qualification, appointed by the Archbishop of Canterbury. The rules which affect Notaries are very similar to the rules which affect Solicitors.</p>\r\n<h2>What can a Notary do?</h2>\r\n<p>A Notary&rsquo;s work normally involves the preparation and authentication of documents for use abroad, Notaries are recognised internationally, unlike Solicitors. Many notaries do work for commercial firms engaged in international trade, and for private individuals.</p>\r\n<p>The most common tasks are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Preparing and witnessing powers of attorney for use overseas </li>\r\n<li>Dealing with purchase or sale of land and property abroad </li>\r\n<li>Providing documents to deal with the administration of the estate of people who are abroad, or owning property abroad </li>\r\n<li>Authenticating personal documents and information for immigration or emigration purposes, or to work abroad </li>\r\n<li>Authenticating company and business documents and transactions</li>\r\n<li>Dealing with documents for weddings abroad</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Preparing to see a Notary</h2>\r\n<p>Although every case will be different, you will need to ensure:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You make an appointment </li>\r\n<li>You bring evidence of your identity to the appointment, such as at least a current valid passport and driving licence </li>\r\n<li>You understand any documents involved, particularly if it is not in English </li>\r\n<li>You bring any documents to the appointment that are relevant to the matter </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Please <a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/12_VISITING  A NOTARY PUBLIC NOTES FOR CLIENTS.doc?1311348870\" target=\"_blank\">read this guide</a> before coming to see Stephen Gordon, our Notary in Chesterfield</h2>\r\n<h2>What is the cost?</h2>\r\n<p>The fee will be based upon the amount of time that is spent dealing with your matter, however a quotation will be provided in advance. If you would like to make an appointment or for further information, please contact Stephen Gordon on 01246 560560 or sg@bannerjones.co.uk.</p>','2010-11-12 17:14:53','2011-09-26 15:13:02','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Stephen Gordon</p>\r\n<p>Notary Public</p>\r\n<p>Chesterfield</p>','50_Stephen.jpg','image/jpeg',81802,'2011-03-04 10:16:43','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Notary.jpg','image/jpeg',32240,'2011-01-13 14:42:24','Notary Services','','','Notary Services','/team_members/39','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(33,'Family Business','family_owned_business','Family Business',33,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Through the generations...</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Did you know that over 70% of UK businesses are family owned? If you own a family business you&rsquo;ll know just how demanding it can be and that your needs are different to other businesses. Here at Banner Jones we recognise that, and have set up a dedicated Family Business Law team who can offer you tailored, specialist advice to ensure your family business runs smoothly from one generation to the next.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our team are corporate members of the International Centre for Families in Business (ICFIB) and as such have gone through specialist legal training, specifically to meet the needs of Family owned businesses.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/33/contained_images/ec6dbdf69703_31_ICFIB_LOGO_STRAPnew.JPG?1298305782\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"184\" height=\"134\" /></p>','2010-11-12 17:15:19','2012-02-09 16:07:07','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>If you are looking to start a business with a family member then we can advise you on the best way to do this</p>\r\n<p>Call us now</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','100_iStock_000011900095XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',63355,'2011-03-04 11:42:22','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','FamilyBusiness.jpg','image/jpeg',55696,'2010-12-22 09:28:36','Family Business','','','Family Business','','',NULL,'family_highlight','<p>Do you have a Family Business Question?</p>\r\n<p>Click here to access a wealth of family business legal advice</p>','','http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/ownership-and-management/family-businesses','153_The-Law-Donut.jpg','image/jpeg',56338,'2012-02-09 16:06:03',''),(34,'Intellectual Property Protection','intellectual_property_protection','Intellectual property protection',34,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>Beware of copy cats</h2>\r\n<p>They say imitation is the best form of flattery, but would you say that if it was your idea being copied and exploited? &nbsp;Businesses who underestimate the need for Intellectual Property (IP) protection may see their market position eroded quickly &nbsp;as &lsquo;Me Too&rsquo; products and services&nbsp;hit the market.</p>\r\n<p>There are four main types of IP rights which you can use to protect your innovations including Trademarks, Designs, Copyrights and Patents.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Trade marks</strong> are symbols that distinguish goods and services in the marketplace - like logos and brand names. Trademarks prohibit anyone using the logo or brand without authorisation from the owner.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Designs</strong> protect items such as the shape of a take-away cup to the body of jet and these prevent rival companies having exact replicas in the market place.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Copyright</strong> is an automatic right which applies to work that is fixed, such as an original of a novel or article.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Patents</strong> protect what makes things work &ndash; like the latest gadget or the chemical formula of your favourite fizzy drink.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;It is important that you do not tell anyone about your invention before you apply for a patent, because this may make your patent invalid. However, you can tell qualified (registered) lawyers, solicitors and patent agents because anything you say to or show them is legally privileged. If you need to discuss your invention with someone before you apply for a patent, a <strong>confidentiality disclosure agreement</strong> (CDA) or <strong>non-disclosure agreements</strong> (NDA) can help.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Protect your idea today and call our Business Legal Services team on 0333 200 2300</strong></p>\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/intellectual-property/?s=BAN082\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n<p><strong>Click here for additional advice on intellectual property protection</strong></p>\r\n</a><img src=\"../../..//assets/page_contents/34/contained_images/b936f46bd866_153_The-Law-Donut.jpg?1326295165\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"192\" height=\"53\" /></strong>','2010-11-12 17:15:59','2012-01-20 11:19:44','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Need help drawing up contracts for suppliers?</p>','102_iStock_000012393462XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',57204,'2011-03-30 10:37:34','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','IntellectualPropetyProtection.jpg','image/jpeg',46396,'2011-02-15 16:42:10','Intellectual Property Protection','','','Intellectual Property Protection','/page/commercial-agreements','',NULL,'family_highlight','','/page/commercial-agreements','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(35,'Total Legal Care Insurance','total_legal_care_insurance','Total Legal Care Insurance',35,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>What is TLC?</h2>\r\n<p>Total Legal Care (TLC) gives your business a local solicitor &lsquo;on demand&rsquo;, backed up with legal insurance at an affordable fixed monthly cost. Whilst your dedicated Banner Jones solicitor provides you with day to day legal advice (whenever you need it) the insurance part of the scheme is designed to give you comfort in the knowledge that your business is protected from any unexpected legal costs and awards of compensation against you. Most would agree a known monthly cost beats a large future cost every time!</p>\r\n<p>TLC covers you against:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contract disputes</li>\r\n<li>Bad debts </li>\r\n<li>Compliance and regulation</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/employment-disputes\">Employment disputes</a></li>\r\n<li>Employment compensation</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/intellectual-property-protection\">Property protection</a></li>\r\n<li>Tax protection </li>\r\n<li>And much more&hellip;.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Prevention is always cheaper than cure (ask any doctor) and in an age of litigation the chances of being involved in an expensive excursion to the courts is not longer remote (employment claims tribunals have increased by 40% since the credit crunch began).&nbsp; Legal representation can cost thousands of pounds, even if you win.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Take surprises off your balance sheet by giving your business a little TLC.&nbsp; TLC is a legal breakdown, assistance and recovery service for businesses and its directors. You insure your car and buildings against damages so why not insure your bottom line?</p>\r\n<h2>Why do you need it?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You can call your dedicated commercial solicitor for advice at any time (now that&rsquo;s something you won&rsquo;t hear very often!) and most of your legal advice and potential costs will either be pre-paid or covered by your TLC insurance policy. Unless you can ring-fence legal costs the impact of a legal action hanging over your business could force cost-cutting, stop a sale, prevent a dividend being paid or even force you into bankruptcy. TLC allows you to plan ahead for profit</li>\r\n<li>TLC is unique because the advice comes from a Banner Jones solicitor retained by you.&nbsp; Your legal claim is assessed by your solicitor, not someone at a call centre who doesn&rsquo;t even know your business</li>\r\n<li>TLC provides legal funding for both the pursuit and defence of your rights</li>\r\n<li>Both the business entity AND the individual directors are covered unlike many policies</li>\r\n<li>We start the ball rolling with an immediate employment procedure health check and ongoing we will ensure that you are up to date with the latest laws, compliance directives and regulations</li>\r\n<li>You might be thinking &lsquo;We&rsquo;ve already got free legal expenses cover with our business insurance&rsquo;, well just to warn you, if you do, you will probably be told that you are not entitled to claim on the policy because you have already invalidated it by not following the correct procedures. The procedures that TLC will ensure you are aware of from the beginning</li>\r\n</ul>','2010-11-12 17:16:19','2011-03-04 10:37:25','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'Contact us today for a quote','tlc.JPG','image/pjpeg',18280,'2011-03-04 10:37:25','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','TotalLegalCare.jpg','image/jpeg',50514,'2010-12-22 09:30:46','Total Legal Care','','','Total Legal Care','/page/contact-us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(36,'Insolvency','insolvency__family','Personal Insolvency',36,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Is debt dragging you down?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Personal debt is one of the most stressful things anyone will have to deal with in their life and it can have devastating affects on everyone around you.&nbsp; At times like these you want clear advice from an expert who can help every step of the way.&nbsp; One of the first pieces of advice we would give to anyone in this situation is don&rsquo;t leave it too late, deal with it now.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You might want to consider chasing some of the debts owed to you as a starting point, depending on the circumstances of your debt.&nbsp; Our &nbsp;team can help you do this.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Quite often just receiving a letter from a solicitor can be enough to make a&nbsp;debtor pay up.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you feel there is no way back from the debt there are two main options available to you <strong></strong></p>','2010-11-15 10:27:05','2011-11-29 14:48:06','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<h3>FIXED FEE DEBT RECOVERY SERVICE</h3>\r\n<p>FIRST LETTER FREE*</p>','83_iStock_000007854419XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',99712,'2011-04-14 15:48:51','','business_highlight','red_curve_pic_1.jpg','image/jpeg',66916,'2010-11-19 15:24:50','','Insolvency.jpg','image/jpeg',44533,'2011-01-18 17:10:28','Insolvency','Balance sheet insolvency Having negative net assets &ndash; in other words, liabilities exceed assets. A business may be \'cash flow insolvent\' but \'balance sheet solvent\' if it holds illiquid assets, particularly against short term debt that it cannot immediately realize if called upon to do so. Conversely, a business can have negative net assets showing on its balance sheet but still be cash flow solvent if ongoing revenue is able to meet debt obligations, and thus avoid default &ndash; for instance, if it holds long term debt. Many large companies operate permanently in this state. Insolvency is not a synonym for bankruptcy, which is a determination of insolvency made by a court of law with resulting legal orders intended to resolve the insolvency.','Insolvency is not a synonym for bankruptcy, which is a determination of insolvency made by a court of law with resulting legal orders intended to resolve the insolvency.','Insolvency','/page/debt-recovery-family','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(37,'Bankruptcy','bankruptcy','Clear your mind... and your debt',37,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is often the case that the best solution for insurmountable debt is personal bankruptcy. The law now provides that in most normal circumstances an individual bankrupt for the first time is automatically discharged from bankruptcy after only 12 months. In some cases it can be less!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">During that time you will be able to maintain a job and a bank account and such proportion of your income that is required to meet the reasonable needs of yourself and your family. Once your bankruptcy ends all of your debts (except for some specific ones such as secured debts, student loans and others) are gone.</p>\r\nIt is likely that the number of bankruptcies during the next year will increase dramatically and therefore there should be no personal embarrassment or stigma attached to this solution. There are some restrictions on the activities you can undertake as a bankrupt however, bankruptcy is not the only solution and so seeking the right advice at the right time is crucial.','2010-11-15 10:27:42','2011-04-14 15:51:43','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>If your family circumstances are changing you should review your Will</p>\r\n<p>Contact us now</p>','65_iStock_000002761784XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',140936,'2011-04-14 15:51:43','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Bankruptcy.jpg','image/jpeg',40790,'2011-01-13 14:45:36','Bankruptcy','','','Bankruptcy','/web/contact_us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(38,'IVA','iva','The alternative to bankruptcy',38,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">An Individual Voluntary Arrangement&nbsp;can&nbsp;help you to avoid bankruptcy by entering into an agreement with your unsecured creditors. A proposal is put to your creditors (the people you owe) and if 75% of the value of debts owed vote in favour of the proposal then all of your unsecured debt is rolled into the arrangement.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Normally you will then pay a monthly amount into your agreement usually for a period of 5 years and your creditors receive payment out of those sums. So long as you stick to the terms of the agreement once it comes to an end the debts will be satisfied in full notwithstanding the fact that you may not have actually paid 100% of what you owed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This solution avoids the stigma associated with&nbsp;bankruptcy and also ensures your home is protected from any unsecured creditors.</p>','2010-11-15 10:29:24','2011-04-14 15:55:12','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Selling your house?</p>\r\n<p>We can help</p>','62_iStock_000002026541XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',253141,'2011-04-14 15:55:11','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','IVA.jpg','image/jpeg',29624,'2010-12-22 10:07:00','IVA','','','IVA','/page/selling','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(39,'Personal Injury','personal_injury','Had an accident?',39,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>We\'re with you every step of the way&hellip;</h2>\r\n<p>Whether you have suffered an accident yourself or a claim is being made against you , the Banner Jones team of Personal Injury Solicitors are here to help.</p>\r\n<p>Our&nbsp; Claimant&nbsp;&nbsp;team have been involved in claims of all sizes including those resulting from many high profile&nbsp;incidents.</p>\r\n<p>We have recovered several million pounds for clients over the years with the largest individual award obtained for a client to date&nbsp;being &pound;3,275,000.</p>\r\n<p>Our Defendant team have represented Defendants in the defence of various types of claims however, we pride ourselves on our particular specialism in Road Traffic and Transport claims.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/39/contained_images/bcb8d82b0a07_135_personal Injury.jpg?1320769437\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"250\" /></p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/personal-law/personal-injury/?s=BAN082\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For more information on personal injury law please click here</p>\r\n</a><img src=\"../../..//assets/page_contents/39/contained_images/78ff8d76f6c8_153_The-Law-Donut.jpg?1326295165\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"231\" height=\"71\" />','2010-11-15 10:29:39','2012-01-20 12:10:54','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>NO Fee Win or Lose</p>\r\n<p>100% of compensation awarded</p>\r\n<p>Free initial consultation</p>\r\n<p>Expert Solicitors, not claims managers</p>','crutches.JPG','image/pjpeg',108807,'2011-03-24 16:25:29','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','PersonalInjury.jpg','image/jpeg',40573,'2011-01-18 17:09:40','Personal Injury','','','Personal Injury','','',2,'family_highlight','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(40,'Claims','claims','Personal Injury Claims',40,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p><strong>Let us help you.</strong>&nbsp; If you&rsquo;ve suffered an injury as a result of an accident that wasn&rsquo;t your fault then the&nbsp;Banner Jones team of Personal Injury Solicitors are here to help you.</p>\r\n<p>We know how traumatic the effects of an accident can be and why early and clear advice is so important. We will provide an initial <strong>free assessment </strong>of your case including providing our views on the prospects of success and the likely timescale.</p>\r\n<p>In most cases we will pursue claims on a &ldquo;<strong>no win, no fee</strong>&rdquo; basis&nbsp;and you will keep <strong>100% of the compensation</strong>, however we will consider all possible methods of funding including legal aid, legal expenses insurance, trade union funding and private fee agreements.</p>\r\n<p>Our specialised team of Personal Injury&nbsp;Solicitors&nbsp;have been involved claims resulting from many high profile&nbsp;incidents including :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hatfield Rail Crash</li>\r\n<li>The Manchester Air Crash</li>\r\n<li>Zeebrugge Ferry Disaster&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We have recovered several million pounds for clients over the years with the largest individual award obtained for a client to date&nbsp;being &pound;3,275,000.</p>\r\n<p>You will normally&nbsp;be entitled to claim for :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Your pain and&nbsp;suffering </li>\r\n<li>Past and future loss of earnings</li>\r\n<li>Travelling and parking costs</li>\r\n<li>Medication and treatment costs</li>\r\n<li>Pension losses</li>\r\n<li>Care and services</li>\r\n<li>Legal and other fees involved in pursuing of your claim</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Typical accidents for which we have successfully claimed compensation for include:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 10:29:57','2011-11-08 16:24:55','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Dial <strong>0333 200 2300</strong></p>\r\n<p>Or click&nbsp;below to e-mail <a href=\"mailto:claim@bannerjones.co.uk\">claim@bannerjones.co.uk</a></p>\r\n<p>START&nbsp;YOUR CLAIM NOW</p>','86_iStock_000008332115XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',52852,'2011-05-09 14:10:56','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Claims.jpg','image/jpeg',34373,'2011-01-13 14:46:08','Claims','','','Claims','','',2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(41,'Defendant','defendant','Got a claim against you?',41,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>We can represent and advise you or your company where a personal injury claim is&nbsp;made against you.</p>\r\n<p>Our experience extends to the defence of many types of claims including employers&rsquo; liability and public liability.</p>\r\n<p>We have a particular specialism in transport claims and regularly represent transportation companies in the defence of claims.</p>\r\n<p>If you need quick and clear advice following a claim then our specialist Personal Injury Team can provide that advice and if necessary carry out a thorough investigation of the claim.&nbsp; We will where appropriate maintain a robust approach to conducting your defence. However in relevant cases we will negotiate on your behalf to achieve as early a settlement as is possible with a view to saving costs.</p>','2010-11-15 10:30:11','2011-03-22 17:19:18','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>If you\'re a transport firm&nbsp;we can help you.&nbsp; Cut out expensive insurance and let us do the rest</p>','107_iStock_000013404152XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',42987,'2011-03-04 16:18:09','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Defendant.jpg','image/jpeg',42892,'2011-01-13 14:46:30','Defendant','','','Defendant','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(42,'Residential Property','residential_property','Residential Conveyancing',42,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Moving house? You\'re in good hands</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Selling your home and buying a new one can be one of the most stressful times in your life, what with choosing an estate agent, instructing a solicitor and getting your house ready for viewings. At Banner Jones in Chesterfield and Sheffield we want to take away some of the pressure and our simplified and refined conveyancing process will do just that. We know from experience that the things you care about when instructing a conveyancer&nbsp;are the cost, the speed of the transaction and their level of assistance and advice.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So why choose Banner Jones?</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Local conveyancing experts in Chesterfield and Sheffield</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Competitive and clear Conveyancing charges. You pay only for what you actually need.&nbsp;&nbsp; </li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">We regularly check our prices so you don\'t have to</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Reduced transaction times as we use the latest case management systems</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The ability to check your&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.bannerjones-interactive.co.uk/\">case online</a>, 24/7.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Text messages sent to you when milestones are met</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">We give you more. Get our <a href=\"../../../page/purchase-plus\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase Plus</a> package <strong>FREE</strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Your transaction will be undertaken by a Specialist Property Lawyer </li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The peace of mind of knowing that all work undertaken by us is covered by Professional Indemnity Insurance</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are able to carry out property transactions anywhere in England and Wales. You will not be required to attend our offices in person</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">We cover all types of property transactions</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If your transaction falls through we will only charge you for the work that has been done</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/personal-law/property-law/?s=BAN082\" target=\"_blank\">For more infomation on residential property law please click here</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/42/contained_images/eac7b2ea2744_153_The-Law-Donut.jpg?1326295165\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"233\" height=\"72\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 10:31:55','2012-03-22 12:53:58','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p><strong>Get you FREE online quote now!</strong></p>','86_iStock_000008332115XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',52852,'2011-03-28 13:53:12','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','ResidentialProperty.jpg','image/jpeg',54276,'2010-12-22 10:13:15','Residential Property','','','Residential Property','/conveyancing_quotes','',NULL,'other_highlight','Proud New Members of the&nbsp;CQS Scheme','/conveyancing_quotes','','167_CQS Logo.JPG','image/jpeg',73870,'2012-03-22 12:51:56',''),(43,'Buying','buying','Buying a House',43,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Had an offer accepted? Congratulations!</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Buying a house is an exciting time for anybody but the process can be a bit daunting&nbsp; so that is&nbsp;why we are here to help you every step of the way.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The&nbsp;steps involved in <strong><a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/4_buying a home process one pages.pdf?1300809818\" target=\"_blank\">buing a house</a> </strong>are relatively straight forward, however, it can get more complex if there are several buyers in the chain. That&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s even more important to instruct a specialist conveyancer who will keep you up to date with progress along the way.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Once you are a client you can keep up to date with your purchase very easily by checking your case on line.&nbsp;Our <a href=\"http://www.bannerjones-interactive.co.uk\" target=\"_blank\">interactive case tracking website</a>allows you to check your progress 24/7 and you will also receive a text message when a milestone has been completed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Aa Thank You for choosing Banner Jones if you are buying a house in Chesterfield of Sheffield you will get our <a href=\"../../../page/purchase-plus\">Purchase Plus</a> package absolutely Free!&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 10:32:16','2011-11-29 14:42:08','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Click here for an instant online conveyancing quote</p>','86_iStock_000008332115XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',52852,'2011-05-16 13:33:25','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Buying.jpg','image/jpeg',35258,'2010-12-22 09:35:48','Buying','','','Buying','/conveyancing_quotes','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(44,'Selling','selling','Selling a House',44,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Are you waiting for that offer?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are many reasons why you may need to sell your home, but whatever your circumstances we&rsquo;ll be with you every step of the way.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The process behind <a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/5_selling a home process one page.pdf?1300809842\" target=\"_blank\">selling your home</a> is not complex but it&rsquo;s important to have a qualified conveyancer on your side for any unforeseen complications that can arise.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are using Banner Jones to sell your house don&rsquo;t forget you can log in now to check your case progress.&nbsp;Our case tracking &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.bannerjones-interactive.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Interactive site</a> allows you to check your &nbsp;progress and you will also&nbsp;receive a text message when a milestone has been completed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are selling your home you will want to get the best price possible for the sale.&nbsp;&nbsp; There are various property websites around that can help you establish what your home might be worth but why not take a look on <a href=\"http://www.zoopla.co.uk/\">www.zoopla.co.uk</a> and see what other houses in your area are selling for?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Complimentary services:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are selling your home due to a marriage breakdown we have a specialist Divorce team who may be able to give you further advice about the division of your assets</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are selling a home as part of a Probate, again we have a specialist team who will be able to advise you and give appropriate tax advice. </li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are selling a property abroad you may need the services of a Notary to legalise the signing of any documents.</li>\r\n</ul>','2010-11-15 10:32:29','2011-11-29 14:42:39','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Click here for an instant online quotation</p>','86_iStock_000008332115XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',52852,'2011-03-24 16:02:26','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Selling.jpg','image/jpeg',70932,'2010-12-22 10:13:57','Selling','','','Selling','/conveyancing_quotes','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(45,'Online Quote','get_a_quote','Get an instant online quote',45,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>Or call us on <strong>0333 200 2300</strong> if you would rather get a quote over the phone.&nbsp;&nbsp;We\'ll gladly&nbsp;talk you through the quote so that &nbsp;you understand exactly what\'s included.</p>\r\n<p>When you are comparing quotes for conveyancing it is very important you know what&rsquo;s included in the price and are comparing like for like. Some firms will give you a cheaper price but then the final price is double/treble that. Every house sale and purchase is different with different levels of searches often required but with our fixed fee promise we can guarantee the price we quote is the price you&rsquo;ll pay (subject to any additional work required during the process).</p>\r\n<h2>What&rsquo;s included in our fees?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Legal Fees (our fee for completing the work)</li>\r\n<li>Administration of the mortgage or secured loan on your purchase</li>\r\n<li>Official Copies of Title</li>\r\n<li>Identification Check</li>\r\n<li>Land Registry Search </li>\r\n<li>Bankruptcy Search</li>\r\n<li>One Telegraphic Bank Transfer Service </li>\r\n<li>Production of Stamp Duty Land Tax Documents</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Disbursements or Third Party Costs&nbsp;will be payable extra.&nbsp; These are not our costs and are fees that we need to pay to complete the transaction for you.</p>\r\n<p>These include the:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Land Registration Fee</li>\r\n<li>Stamp Duty Land Tax (% of the purchase price)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Supplemental fees&nbsp;such as searches will be payable extra but we will confirm all of these prices with you before commiting to the work.</p>','2010-11-15 10:32:43','2011-05-17 13:01:25','','',1,1,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Online Instant Calculator</p>\r\n<p>Fill in your details now for an instant quote</p>','86_iStock_000008332115XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',52852,'2011-05-16 13:21:06','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','OnlineQuote.jpg','image/jpeg',53104,'2011-03-29 12:00:48','Get a Quote','','','Get a Quote','/conveyancing_quotes','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(46,'Property Abroad','property_abroad','Property Abroad',46,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','','2010-11-15 10:32:59','2011-01-21 15:35:58','','',1,1,0,NULL,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','SellingAbroad.jpg','image/jpeg',56822,'2010-12-22 10:14:30','Property Abroad','','','Property Abroad','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(47,'Purchase Plus','purchase_plus','FREE Offer - Worth over £100',47,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Purchase Plus+ includes:</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>A FREE Large Pizza from Domino\'s when you move in</li>\r\n<li>12 months FREE Home Emergency Insurance from Encore</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What\'s included in the cover with Encore?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Your free cover provides real protection in a home emergency situation,<br />saving you both the worry of finding a reliable engineer in a hurry and<br />the expense of large repair bills. Your Encore policy is underwritten by<br />leading insurer Brit Insurance for your peace of mind.<br />Encore Home Emergency cover includes:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Up to &pound;1000 of cover per claim &ndash; including callout, most parts and labour</li>\r\n<li>Unlimited number of claims &ndash; there are no limits to the number of claims that you can make as an Encore member</li>\r\n<li>Access to skilled contractors</li>\r\n<li>The Home Emergency Helpline number is available 24 hours a day, 365 days a year</li>\r\n<li>No bills to pay &ndash; the bill is settled direct with the engineer within the cover limits</li>\r\n<li>Up to &pound;250 towards overnight accommodation &ndash; if you can&rsquo;t stay in your home overnight</li>\r\n<li>Your home will be covered against:</li>\r\n<li>Boiler breakdown resulting in loss of hot water and/or heating</li>\r\n<li>Plumbing and drainage emergencies</li>\r\n<li>The last or only remaining toilet in the property is inoperable</li>\r\n<li>Complete electrical breakdown</li>\r\n<li>Vermin infestation</li>\r\n<li>Security (break in or vandalism that has been reported to the police)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The above is a policy summary, terms and conditions may apply, for full details please ask for a specimen policy. Purchase Plus + is not available in conjunction with any other offer.</p>','2010-11-15 10:33:19','2011-03-24 15:56:35','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">We know you won\'t want to cook on the night you move in so why not have a Domino\'s pizza for FREE?</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">T&amp;C\'s apply</span></h3>','domlogo2.JPG','image/pjpeg',107013,'2011-02-14 14:40:25','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','','/page/purchase-plus','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(48,'Family','family','Family Law',48,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>Here for you</h2>\r\n<h2>We\'re with you every step of the way&hellip;</h2>\r\n<p class=\"Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Banner Jones\'&nbsp;experienced family law team know that you need specialist advice in what may be a difficult and stressful time. We&nbsp;will provide clear guidance and a summary of all your options,&nbsp;of which&nbsp;there may be several.&nbsp;&nbsp; We&rsquo;ll set out your options in plain English and make sure you understand how your case might progress.&nbsp;&nbsp; We&rsquo;ll provide you with support and sensitivity throughout your case but be assured we will&nbsp;also take a strong and robust position when necessary.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have Resolution and Collaborative Law accredited specialists who are trained to the high levels expected of Resolution Specialists. We will endeavour to&nbsp;look for a non-confrontational solution, although in some cases we appreciate that this may not always be possible.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/48/contained_images/0382b63916ed_1_ResolutionSpecialist.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"128\" height=\"105\" /><img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/48/contained_images/d225eab87a00_3_CollaborativeLaw.jpg?1291818343\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"218\" height=\"108\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&ldquo;Advice&rdquo; from friends and family is well meaning, and you need their support, but the information they can give often relates to circumstances which are different to your own and can give you false expectations and mislead you, unintentionally. Always seek professional advice as early as possible so you know exactly where you stand.</p>\r\n<p>We will advise&nbsp;you on the various methods of funding&nbsp;and as to whether or not you are entitled to Legal Aid.&nbsp; You may also benefit from our new&nbsp;<a href=\"../../../page/fixed-fee-divorce\" target=\"_blank\">Fixed Fee</a>&nbsp;packages. We will always provide a clear indication at the outset as to the expected level of fees which may be incurred.</p>\r\n<p>If you need advice regarding your children then we have accredited specialists within our team who are best placed to advise you.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/48/contained_images/2a9b3418cfab_136_children law.jpg?1320769561\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"250\" /></p>','2010-11-15 10:33:52','2011-11-29 14:41:01','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p><strong>We have one of the largest Family law teams in</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>NE Derbyshire and Sheffield</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>We can help you </strong></p>','125_S0152516.JPG','image/jpeg',264745,'2011-08-11 15:12:40','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Family.jpg','image/jpeg',41531,'2011-01-18 17:10:22','Family','','','Family','/team_members','',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(49,'Divorce and Separation','divorce_and_seperation','Specialist Divorce Solicitors',49,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>Need to get out of your relationship?</h2>\r\n<p>You are probably worrying about where you are going to live, whether you\'ll keep your children and how much money you will have. Don\'t worry we are here to help you with all the legal issues that arise when relationships break up. Whether you are married, or have been living with your partner, our experienced team will advise you on resolving these&nbsp;issues and help you get the best outcome to suit your needs.</p>\r\n<p>Many of our clients also worry about going to Court when they come to see us, but be assured that there are several options available that will avoid you going to Court. Collaborative law is one of the modern approaches to family breakdown and has been labelled as a &ldquo;good&rdquo; divorce as you agree from the outset that you will not go to Court.&nbsp; We do appreciate however, that not all cases are the same and if going to Court is your chosen route then we\'ll be with you every step of the way.</p>\r\n<h2>Why choose Banner Jones Solicitors?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We have one of the largest Family Law teams in NE Derbyshire and Sheffield</li>\r\n<li>You have a choice of&nbsp;5 offices across Chesterfield, Bolsover, Clay Cross, Dronfield and Sheffield</li>\r\n<li>We have a mixed team of male and female divorce lawyers so if you have a preference then you can choose who you see</li>\r\n<li>We are experienced in high value matrimonial cases</li>\r\n<li>We are Resolution accredited</li>\r\n<li>We have Collaborative lawyers in our team</li>\r\n<li>We have Children law specialists in our team</li>\r\n<li>We have an independent mediation service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If your financial&nbsp;circumstances&nbsp;are complex and you need advice on the division of high value matrimonial assets and property, &nbsp;then we have the experience to help you reach the best solution.</p>\r\n<p>Some couples are able to resolve their situation amicably through <a href=\"../../../page/mediation\">Mediation</a>. Could this be right for you?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/personal-law/cohabitation-separation-and-divorce/?s=BAN082\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n<p>For more information on cohabitation, separation and divorce please click here</p>\r\n</a><img src=\"../../..//assets/page_contents/49/contained_images/b6a273f90988_153_The-Law-Donut.jpg?1326295165\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"203\" height=\"49\" />','2010-11-15 10:34:24','2012-01-20 12:09:15','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p><strong>NEW Fixed Fee Divorce</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Giving you the choice...</strong></p>','65_iStock_000002761784XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',140936,'2011-07-22 15:14:31','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DivorceAndSeparation.jpg','image/jpeg',56028,'2011-01-13 16:16:24','Divorce and Separation','','','Divorce and Separation','/page/fixed-fee-divorce','',5,'family_highlight','','/page/fixed-fee-divorce','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(50,'Children','children','What about the kids?',50,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>You know your children better than anyone else and as a parent you are best placed to make the important decisions for them, but there may be times you need more help, support and guidance.</p>\r\n<p>If you have children and you are getting divorced, separating, or your cohabitation is breaking up, we can advise you on a wide range of issues relating to the children.</p>\r\n<p>As far as possible, we help you reach an amicable agreement which is always based upon what is in the children&rsquo;s &nbsp;best interests. However, where necessary, we can apply to the Courts for appropriate Orders.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For some examples of common issues and problems and how we can assist you click on the link.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../../../page/parental-responsibility\" target=\"_blank\">Parental Responsibility </a>-what rights and responsibilities do both parents have</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../../../page/residence-orders\" target=\"_blank\">Residence Orders</a> - where should the children live and who should be the children&rsquo;s primary carer</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../../../page/contact-orders\" target=\"_blank\">Contact Orders</a> - what time should the children spend with each adult</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../../../page/mediation\" target=\"_blank\">Mediation</a> -non-court based process with trained neutral mediators</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../../../page/collaborative-law\" target=\"_blank\">Collaborative law</a> -non-court based lawyer supported negotiation</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../../../page/applying-to-court\" target=\"_blank\">Applying to Court</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../../../page/care-proceedings\" target=\"_blank\">Care Proceedings</a>- where there is social services intervention in the Children&rsquo;s care</p>\r\n<p>Helena Downing, Kevin Tomlinson and Diane Gunn are all on the Law Society\'s Children&rsquo;s panel. Only solicitors who meet the Law Society&rsquo;s exacting accreditation requirements are permitted to join the Children Panel and represent children in public law care proceedings.&nbsp; Your skills, knowledge and experience are rigorously and independently assessed in order to achieve this accreditation status. This means that you know you are dealing with the very best .</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/50/contained_images/f16c92303bc3_136_children law.jpg?1320769561\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"250\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">For a Fixed Fee Interview, which includes a free half hour please contact us today</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 10:34:39','2012-02-24 14:26:06','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Fixed Fee Interview</p>\r\n<p><strong>First 30 Minutes FREE</strong></p>','158_woman and child.jpg','image/jpeg',274596,'2012-02-24 14:26:05','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Children.jpg','image/jpeg',53936,'2011-01-13 14:48:27','Children','','','Children','/web/contact_us','',NULL,'family_highlight','','/web/contact_us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(51,'Cohabitation','cohabitation','Does not being married worry you?',51,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Break-up of a relationship</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The law treats unmarried couples differently from married couples. Our knowledge of this complex area of law can help you resolve your problems following break-up with a cohabitation partner.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Much can be done to protect your interests, including your financial assets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If there are children from the relationship, we can help you to agree arrangements for them.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cohabitation agreements</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Did you know that...</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is no such thing as a &ldquo;common law&rdquo; husband and wife? </li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If a co-habitee dies the survivor is not his or her &ldquo;next of kin&rdquo; and therefore may have to go to court to claim all or any of the deceased&rsquo;s estate? </li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">You may not automatically be responsible for any surviving children of the relationship? </li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">A co-habitee does not automatically acquire an interest in his or her partner&rsquo;s property simply by living there for a certain period of time; and that the law in this area is so complex that some Judges struggle to make sense of it? </li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Even if you own property together, you may not own it equally (especially if it was bought before 1996) and that a recent case has stated that, in certain situations, the value of that house may not automatically be shared equally between former co-habitees? </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A Cohabitation agreement can help remove some of the above uncertainties. If you are going to live with a partner but not marry, it is sensible to create an agreement which records your intentions about your assets and how you would share or divide them if your relationship broke up. We can draft an agreement which states your intentions and protects your financial assets.</p>','2010-11-15 10:34:57','2011-04-14 15:26:06','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Protect your assets with a Will</p>','43_hand and keys.JPG','image/jpeg',53480,'2011-04-14 15:26:06',NULL,'family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Cohabitation.jpg','image/jpeg',52209,'2011-01-13 14:48:45','Cohabitation','','','Cohabitation','/page/making-a-will','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(52,'Domestic Violence','domestic_violence','You are not on your own',52,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We respond quickly if you are suffering violence from anyone with whom you have a domestic relationship, or have been in the past. It may be your spouse, partner, or even your child. The violence may be physical or psychological.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our approach will be to consider how best to protect you. This may involve making an application for an injunction from the court in order to stop the person coming near you. It may carry a Power of Arrest to give you effective protection.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you need a solicitor to act for you quickly, telephone us on 01246 209773.</p>','2010-11-15 10:35:14','2011-02-28 12:04:16','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'Take a look at Women\'s Aid for additional help and support.','logo.gif','image/gif',1996,'2011-01-21 14:50:59','Women\'s Aid Logo','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DomesticViolence.jpg','image/jpeg',53960,'2011-01-13 14:49:03','Domestic Violence','','','Domestic Violence','','http://www.womensaid.org.uk',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(53,'Pre or Postmarital/Partnership Agreements','pre_marital_agreements','Do I need one?',53,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With high profile cases such as the Mills and McArtney raising the profile of acrimonious settlements, it is little surprise that couples thinking of marrying would now give consideration to some sort of pre marital prenuptial agreements.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Who should consider a pre or post-marital/partnership agreement?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Agreements of this nature are particularly worth considering if:-</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>One or both of the parties to the relationship are more mature. </li>\r\n<li>Where this may be his second marriage or partnership. </li>\r\n<li>Where one party brings significant assets to a relationship or there is an imbalance in the financial provision to be made by both parties. </li>\r\n<li>Where provision needs to be made for children or dependants from a previous relationship. </li>\r\n<li>Where you wish to influence how assets may be divided between you should the marriage or civil partnership fail.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">When should we consider these types of agreements?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As soon as possible. The longer the agreement is in place prior to a marriage or civil partnership being entered into the better. However, agreements entered into after marriage or Civil Partnership can still have legal effect.&nbsp; In order for an agreement of this nature to be made binding there needs to be independent legal advice for both parties, full and frank financial disclosure and no duress.&nbsp; If a pre-nuptial agreement of this nature is entered into at the church door then it is open to an allegation that one party or the other has been under a level of duress to enter into the agreement.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Are pre or postnuptial agreements binding?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Prenuptial agreements are common place on mainland Europe but the courts in England and Wales have always been reluctant to have their overall discretion as to how assets should be divided upon divorce tied in by an agreement reached between two parties prior to the marriage taking place.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A gradual shift towards recognising the validity of pre and post nuptial agreements was brought to a head by the case of <strong>Radmacher v. Grantino</strong>. This case went to the highest court in the land, The Supreme Court, purely on whether a pre-nuptial agreement entered into by the parties in Germany three months before they married was applicable in law in England and Wales.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Supreme Court decided in October 2010 that it was natural to infer that parties entering into agreements of this sort will intend that legal effect would be given to those agreements. Unless the outcome of the pre-nuptial agreement was unfair to any children of the marriage, in which case the court could still ignore or vary the agreement, the agreement would be upheld by the court.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">How do I found out more?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Please contact any member of the family team who would be able to discuss the options available with you.</p>','2010-11-15 10:35:37','2011-04-14 15:28:15','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Contacts us today to get your agreement in place</p>','58_iStock_000000753188XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',144736,'2011-03-04 16:11:24','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','PartnershipAgreements.jpg','image/jpeg',42618,'2011-01-13 14:49:43','Pre or Postmarital/Partnership Agreements','','','Pre or Postmarital/Partnership Agreements','/web/contact_us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(54,'Civil Partnerships','civil_partnerships','The facts uncovered',54,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What are Civil Partnerships?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Civil partnerships are for adult same sex couples who are not in existing registered partnerships or marriage and are not closely related.&nbsp; Couples who register have legal status as &ldquo;registered civil partners&rdquo; and acquire a package of rights and responsibilities in the same way as a married couple.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What happens if my Civil Partnership does not work?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If the civil partnership breaks down then you can apply to the court to have the partnership brought to an end after you have been together as civil partners for at least one year.&nbsp;&nbsp; This is known as a Dissolution.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">How do I end my Civil Partnership?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bringing the relationship to an end involves the similar process to having a divorce.&nbsp; A petition is filed asking that the partnership should be brought to a conclusion and showing that the partnership has definitely come to an end.&nbsp; The petition will need to be lodged with a County Court that specifically deals with dissolving civil partnerships.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What basis can the partnership be ended by the Court?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The court will accept similar grounds to prove that the relationship has come to an end as those of divorcing couples.&nbsp; The ground for dissolution is that the relationship has broken down irretrievably shown by the following facts:-</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Either that your civil partner&rsquo;s behaviour has been so unreasonable you can no longer bear to live with him or her;</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">That you or your civil partner have lived apart for at least two years immediately preceding the presentation of the petition and your partner agrees to a dissolution;</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">That you and your civil partner have lived apart for at least five years prior to the presentation of the petition and the partner&rsquo;s consent is not required, or;</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;Your civil partner has deserted you.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For a desertion petition you will need to have been apart for two years immediately preceding the presentation of the petition.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Can I make financial claims against my civil partner if the partnership is brought to a conclusion?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Civil partners can make claims against each other&rsquo;s finances in the same way that heterosexual married couples can.&nbsp; If there are financial issues stemming from your separation and dissolution of the partnership you will need to take further detailed advice and we recommend that you contact one of the family team who can give you specific advice in relation to this complex area of law.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What if there are children involved?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Following a dissolution we can apply to the Courts&nbsp; for orders&nbsp;regarding&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; children issues including residence, contact order and financial provision.&nbsp; See our <a href=\"../../../page/children\" target=\"_blank\">Children</a> page for more details.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Are there any useful sites for me to look at?</h2>\r\n<p>We recommended you look at the following websites:-</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.stonewall.org.uk/\">www.stonewall.org.uk</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmcourts-service.gov.uk\">www.hmcourts-service.gov.uk</a> to look at the paperwork involved in dissolving the civil partnership</p>','2010-11-15 10:35:57','2012-01-30 16:13:18','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Protect your assets with a Will</p>\r\n<p>Don\'t leave it too late</p>','102_iStock_000012393462XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',57204,'2011-04-14 15:30:19','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','CivilPartnerships.jpg','image/jpeg',51597,'2011-01-13 14:51:20','Civil Partnerships','','','Civil Partnerships','/page/making-a-will','',NULL,'family_highlight','','/page/making-a-will','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(61,'Criminal Defence','crime','Criminal Defence',61,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">We\'re on your side...</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our highly regarded Criminal Defence team represent defendants in all types of cases including:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Theft and Fraud</li>\r\n<li>Burglary and Robbery</li>\r\n<li>Assault and Wounding</li>\r\n<li>Possession and Supply of drugs</li>\r\n<li>Firearms offences</li>\r\n<li>Rape, Manslaughter and Murder</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Several members of our criminal defence team are accredited by the Law Society\'s Criminal Litigation panel which means that&nbsp;they have gone through rigorous checks and can offer you the very best in advice.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/61/contained_images/e9c9dfd555a5_138_crim lit.JPG?1320854744\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"250\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Police Station</strong> &ndash; we have accredited Police Station Representatives who will give expert legal advice to those in police custody on a 24-hour basis. If you need to contact a duty solicitor out of hours please call our criminal emergency number <strong>07973 225894</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Magistrates Court</strong> &ndash; we support each client, make thorough preparations, and provide advocacy or instruct a barrister on your behalf</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Crown Court</strong> &ndash; we provide advice and support including the preparation of the case, gathering witness statements, and briefing your barrister.</p>\r\n<strong>Legal Aid</strong> &ndash; Many of our clients are entitled to Legal Aid. If costs have to be paid on a private basis, we give an estimate of the likely costs at the outset.','2010-11-15 10:52:51','2011-11-29 14:48:55','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p><strong>Out of Hours help number </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>07973 225 894</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Call our duty solicitor on this number if you need support out of office hours</strong></p>','88_iStock_000008392789XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',232600,'2011-03-04 16:43:48','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','CriminalDefence.jpg','image/jpeg',28550,'2011-07-29 14:28:58','Criminal Defence','','','Criminal Defence','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62,'Wills','wills','Wills',62,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 class=\"Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Thinking about the unthinkable</h2>\r\n<p class=\"Banner20Jones20PresentationLTGliederung1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Making a Will is often seen as a daunting prospect for a lot of people but here at Banner Jones we&rsquo;ll take you through it step by step ensuring that your Will represents everything you want it to.&nbsp; Most of our clients say it&rsquo;s such a relief to have finally done it and usually they have been putting it off for ages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Making a Will is commonly associated as something you do in later life however, in reality anyone over the age of 18 can have a Will and we would strongly recommend it to anyone with children.&nbsp;&nbsp; Wills are not for just sorting out finances and property in the event of your death, you can appoint guardians for your children and even leave money to your friends or a charity.&nbsp; Without a Will the government decides these things for you.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Read our <a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/14_Factsheet - 10 Reasons why you need a Will.doc?1322580008\" target=\"_blank\">free guide</a>&nbsp;now which will give you 10 reasons why you should have a Will.</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Why Use Banner Jones?</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Highly regarded team of qualified Wills solicitors</li>\r\n<li>FREE secure Will storage for life</li>\r\n<li>Members of \'the Certainty\' national Will register</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://c.eu1.content.force.com/servlet/servlet.EmailAttachmentDownload?q=P4yZkOaHZ2naG%2FUwJ%2BJo7d5f0gCX7aBOfFdiE2DZyyvyNLP5qjSuiVD6wnfqarWdlSerSgl5Le%2FO2vj%2F%2Fq9WtQ%3D%3D\" alt=\"\" width=\"241\" height=\"88\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Appointments not always necessary</li>\r\n<li>Quick turnaround</li>\r\n<li>Home visits available</li>\r\n<li>Witnesses provided</li>\r\n<li>We\'ll give you tax advice as part of the process</li>\r\n<li>Fixed Fee Promise on all Wills</li>\r\n<li>We will cover every detail leaving you able to relax</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Make an appointment today</p>','2010-11-15 10:53:07','2012-09-12 12:14:57','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Solicitors are insured and regulated.</p>\r\n<p>Will writers are not.</p>\r\n<p>Protect your family properly</p>','84_iStock_000007985661XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',174578,'2011-03-04 16:19:43','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Wills.jpg','image/jpeg',51009,'2011-01-12 13:00:19','Wills','','','Wills','/page/making-a-will','',NULL,'family_highlight','<p>Register your Will today</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Our Wills now include FREE registration on the national Will register, Certainty</p>','/page/making-a-will','','CertaintyNewLogo.JPG','image/jpeg',44741,'2012-06-12 12:16:56',''),(63,'Making a Will','making_a_will','Making a Will',63,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>Writing a Will could be the most important thing you\'ll ever do.</h2>\r\n<h2>Not sure where to start?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To help get you started here are a few things to think about when preparing to write your Will.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Your Estate</h3>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Make a list of everything you own and what it is worth (assets)</li>\r\n<li>Include any life insurance policies and pension assets (if not already assigned)</li>\r\n<li>Subtract any money you may owe on death, such as mortgages and loans (liabilities)</li>\r\n<li>Estimate how much your estate is likely to be (the difference between your assets and liabilities)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Beneficiaries</h3>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Make a list of those whom you want to benefit, including names and addresses.&nbsp; Think about any&nbsp;wider family and friends also</li>\r\n<li>Think about who you would like to be guardians for your children and seek their approval</li>\r\n<li>Think about whether you want to leave gifts to any charities. See our <a href=\"../../../page/legacies\" target=\"_blank\">legacies</a>&nbsp;page for more information</li>\r\n<li>Make a note of who you DON\'T want to benefit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Once you have all of this information you are ready to start drafting your Will</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Appointments are not always necessary -<a href=\"../../../page/contact-us\" target=\"_blank\">CALL US NOW</a></p>\r\n<h2>Reviewing your Will</h2>\r\n<p>Circumstances change over time so we advise that our clients review their Will every 5 years to ensure it still meets their needs. For example you may have moved house, gone through a divorce or maybe even had more Children/Grandchildren in that time.&nbsp; Some people may change their Will several times over their lifetime and there is no limit to how many times you can do this.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/personal-law/wills-and-probate/?s=BAN082\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n<p>For more FREE information on making a Will please click here</p>\r\n</a><img src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/63/contained_images/0e10a936f499_153_The-Law-Donut.jpg?1326295165\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"231\" height=\"67\" />','2010-11-15 10:55:49','2012-06-12 12:18:57','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Starting a Family?</p>\r\n<p>It\'s time to write&nbsp;a Will</p>','82_iStock_000007694576XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',124876,'2011-03-28 14:47:21','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','MakingAWill.jpg','image/jpeg',50736,'2011-01-11 11:51:49','Making a Will','','','Making a Will','','',NULL,'family_highlight','All of our Wills now include FREE registration on to the national Will register, Certainty','','','170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG','image/jpeg',44954,'2012-06-12 12:18:56',''),(64,'Buy Online','buy_online','Buy Online',64,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>Making a Will is much easier than most people think and we&rsquo;ve made it even easier by giving you a choice of how you go about it.<strong>&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Buy      Online. Make a standard Will today. Fill out the forms online and we&rsquo;ll check over the document for you and make sure that it suits your      needs.</li>\r\n<li>By      Appointment. Visit us in one of our offices to go through your wishes in      detail with a solicitor.&nbsp; This      option is best if you need tax planning advice or are looking to set up      trusts in your Will.</li>\r\n</ol> We come to your home or care home and take your wishes from you, sending the Will out to you for signatures.','2010-11-15 10:56:10','2011-01-21 15:44:25','','',1,1,0,NULL,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','BuyOnline.jpg','image/jpeg',35538,'2011-01-11 11:43:45','Buy Online','','','Buy Online','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65,'Legacies','legacies','A gift in your Will',65,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Leaving money to charity in your Will can be a very satisfying thing to do, perhaps because they&rsquo;ve helped you or your loved ones in the past and you want to thank them for their hard work by leaving them a gift.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are two ways you can decide to leave money.&nbsp; You can&nbsp; leave either a residuary gift which is a % share&nbsp;of your final estate (once your family have been provided for), or&nbsp;you can specify the amount of money you wish to leave (A pecuniary gift).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">All gifts to charity in your Will are exempt from Inheritance Tax.&nbsp; These gifts are taken out of your estate before any inheritance tax is worked out, so there may be times when a gift to charity could substantially reduce the tax on your estate.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We work in partnership with several different charities and you could help us to help them by leaving a gift in your Will.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<hr />\r\n<br /><a href=\"http://www.wphcc.org.uk/legacy\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"../../../assets/page_contents/65/contained_images/ffbae737d4fa_13_wphcc.gif?1295369771\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"250\" /></a>\r\n<p>Leaving a gift in your will to the Cancer Charity will have huge benefits not only for patients being treated now, but also for those who will be treated in the future.</p>\r\n<p>It is a simple process to leave a legacy to Weston Park Hospital Cancer Charity, either by making a Will if you do not have one, or by amending your existing Will.</p>\r\n<p>To talk to us about this, or any other aspect of Wills, please <a href=\"../../../web/contact_us\">contact us</a> today</p>','2010-11-15 10:56:23','2011-03-04 16:20:50','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'Did you know over 50% of some charities income comes from the legacies people leave in their Will?','85_iStock_000008248810XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',73750,'2011-03-04 16:20:50','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Legacies.jpg','image/jpeg',44462,'2011-01-11 11:51:03','Legacies','','','Legacies','/page/making-a-will','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66,'Probate','probate','Probate Solicitors',66,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To be able to administer the wishes set out in a Will you will need to apply for probate (technically known as applying for a Grant of Probate or granting of probate).</p>\r\nApplying for Probate is an order of the Court giving one or more people the legal authority to administer the estate of the deceased in order to distribute it correctly to the beneficiaries (i.e. probate of will).<br />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have any asset worth over &pound;5,000, any stocks and shares or a property then your executors will usually need to apply for probate. If you don&rsquo;t make a Will, they need to apply for Letters of Administration instead, which is very similar. A probate valuation will help you find out what your assets are worth.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Unless your assets are all owned jointly with someone else and will pass to them automatically, you will need a Probate solicitor before your estate can be paid out. We can provide detailed advice about this if you need it.</p>\r\n<p>With our Fixed Fee promise after discussing the case with you we will fix your fee for our probate assistance so you know exactly what you will pay from the start.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have thought about how to probate yourself then please be aware that you will be required to attend a personal interview at the Probate Registery in Sheffield.&nbsp; As solicitors we can prepare the oath for you (at a lower fee) as part of our probate services which then saves you an additional&nbsp;trip to the Registery.</p>\r\n<p>To take advantage of our probate adisory service by contacting us now.</p>','2010-11-15 10:56:37','2011-08-16 09:48:11','','',1,3,0,NULL,1,0,'If you need to sell a home as part of the probate we can help you with this','62_iStock_000002026541XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',253141,'2011-03-23 12:26:49','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Probate.jpg','image/jpeg',64373,'2011-01-11 11:52:24','Probate','','','Probate','/page/selling','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(67,'Inheritance Tax','inheritance_tax','Inheritance Tax- the facts',67,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Currently Inheritance Tax&nbsp; is a tax payable on death at the rate of 40% on the value of your net assets over &pound;325,000.&nbsp; &nbsp;The first &pound;325,000 is called the Nil Rate Band because although it is taxable to Inheritance Tax, it is taxed at 0%.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are married, the best way to pay less inheritance tax (or even none at all) is by making inheritance tax efficient Wills.&nbsp; We can help you do this.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Here are some Frequently Asked Questions</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">1. Can&rsquo;t I just give some assets away, so I leave less than the Nil Rate Band when I die?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you give away large amounts of money, or valuable assets whilst you are alive, you must survive this gift for 7 years otherwise the Inland Revenue will tax you as if you still owned them when you die. This is the case whether you make the gift to an individual or put it into some types of trust.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you put your money or assets into certain types of trust or give them to a company, however, there is an immediate charge to inheritance tax &ndash; even though you are still alive.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">2. So, I can&rsquo;t give anything away whilst I am alive unless I survive for 7 years?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are certain gifts you can make which are not subject to this 7 year rule. Everyone has an &ldquo;annual exemption&rdquo; for inheritance tax of &pound;3,000 each every tax year. That means you can give away &pound;3,000 in total every tax year and it immediately falls out of your estate for inheritance tax purposes. If you die within 7 years, that gift will not be brought back into account. If you haven&rsquo;t used your annual exemption one year, you can roll it forward for 1 tax year, so you can give away &pound;6,000 the next year. You can only do this once, however.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">All gifts to UK charity, registered housing associations, qualifying political parties, national museums and universities are also exempt form inheritance tax altogether, whether you give to them under your Will or during your lifetime.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If your children or grandchildren get married, you can give them or their new spouse a lump sum of &pound;5,000 or &pound;2,500 respectively, completely free of inheritance tax.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can give any amount to your own spouse free of inheritance tax (provided you are both domiciled in England and Wales) although you should seek legal advice before doing so, as this could affect other tax planning possibilities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are other gifts which are exempt from inheritance tax &ndash; please telephone or call into one of our offices to arrange an appointment and we will be happy to discuss these further.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">3. If I do decide to give a large amount to my children now, is there anything I can do to reduce the tax?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can insure the inheritance tax liability which would arise if you were to die within 7 years of the gift. Please ask for more information and one of our specialist advisers will be delighted to explain how this works and, if you wish, put you in touch with a trusted financial expert to help you choose the right policy for you.</p>','2010-11-15 10:57:46','2012-01-20 12:20:42','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>For more FREE information on Trusts and Inheritance Tax please click here</p>','78_iStock_000006000433XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',189291,'2011-03-04 16:21:53','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','InheritanceTax.jpg','image/jpeg',35556,'2011-01-11 11:47:27','Inheritance Tax','','','Inheritance Tax','','http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/personal-law/family-trusts-and-inheritance-tax/?s=BAN082',NULL,'family_highlight','','/page/retirement-planning','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(68,'Trusts','trusts','A good way to protect your assets',68,0,0,0,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trusts can be used as a way of protecting your assets.&nbsp;&nbsp;They allow for property and assets to be held by trustees for the benefit of one or more individuals - these can be adult or children.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; These individuals are known as the beneficiaries.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Commonly trusts are set up for assets to be held for the benefit of children until they reach a certain age.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trusts are&nbsp;taxed independently for income tax, capital gains tax and inheritance tax purposes. This makes them an effective means of separating your estate to avoid tax.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A trust means that you assign responsibility of the finances over to a trustee. Trustees have various duties and powers which are given to them either by the general law, the Trust deed (or Will) or a combination of both. It is essential that a Trustee understands the duties imposed on him and the powers available.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To read our free guide of these duties <a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/9_Factsheet - Trustees responsibilities.doc?1300882723\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This can be quite a demanding role and you should know what&rsquo;s involved before agreeing to become a trustee.</p>','2010-11-15 10:58:00','2011-03-23 15:50:10','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>We can involve Independent Financial Advisers in our discussions at no extra cost to you</p>\r\n<p>Just ask</p>','77_iStock_000005896679XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',115487,'2011-03-04 16:24:31','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Trusts.jpg','image/jpeg',57223,'2011-01-11 11:53:36','Trusts','','','Trusts','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(69,'Probate and Estates','probate_and_estates','Probate Specialists',69,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Here for you and your family</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Losing a loved one is one of the most difficult times in our lives and now more than ever you need to know you are working with people who understand your situation and can advise you of the best way to proceed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Banner Jones Probate team can assist you in administering the&nbsp;estate and can provide the advice and support&nbsp;that you need.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have been appointed as someone&rsquo;s executor, it is often difficult at this distressing time to know what to do first.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;Briefly, the steps you need to take initially are:-</p>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Find the Will</li>\r\n<li>Register the death</li>\r\n<li>Arrange the funeral</li>\r\n<li>Secure the deceased&rsquo;s property</li>\r\n<li>Collect together all the paperwork you can find</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For more information click here to read our&nbsp;<a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/6_What to do when someone dies FD version.pdf?1300810419\" target=\"_blank\">free guide</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 10:58:16','2012-09-12 12:14:17','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'Fixed Fee Probate Available Now','108_iStock_000013859617XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',98164,'2011-03-04 16:22:40','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','ProbateAndEstates.jpg','image/jpeg',69792,'2011-01-28 16:21:51','Probate and Estates','','','Probate and Estates','','',NULL,'family_highlight','<p>We can help you locate a Will&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Banner Jones are members of Certainty, a national Will register</p>','','','170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG','image/jpeg',44954,'2012-06-12 12:31:37',''),(70,'Services for the Elderly','services_for_the_elderly','Services for the Elderly',70,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Here for you in later life</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We know that when faced with sorting out your parent\'s affairs (or indeed your own) it can seem like quite a daunting task, after all how do you know you&rsquo;re doing the right thing for them? We at Banner Jones specialise in advising families in what types of things they can look at to make their elderly parent&rsquo;s future secure. With some expert advice and planning you can make sure that their finances are protected from things such as care fees, should that ever be required.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Some of the things you will want to think about are:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Making sure they have an up to date </li>\r\n<li>Creating a <a href=\"../../../page/lasting-power-of-attorney\">lasting power of attorney</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/long-term-care\">Long term care</a> planning to ensure their assets are protected </li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/residential-care-appeals\">Residential care fee appeals</a>&nbsp;if they are already in care and maybe paying too much</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you would like to speak to a solicitor then please contact us to make an appointment.','2010-11-15 10:58:33','2012-06-12 12:30:14','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Do your parents want you to look after everything for them?&nbsp;&nbsp;You can take control of their finances through a&nbsp;Lasting Power of Attorney.</p>\r\n<p>Sort it today</p>','103_iStock_000012395773XSmall (1).jpg','image/jpeg',202247,'2011-03-04 16:25:49','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','ServicesForTheElderly.jpg','image/jpeg',60178,'2011-01-13 14:54:21','Services for the Elderly','','','Services for the Elderly','/page/lasting-power-of-attorney','',NULL,'family_highlight','<p>Register your Will on a national database today, for FREE</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now included in the price of our Wills</p>','/page/lasting-power-of-attorney','','170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG','image/jpeg',44954,'2012-06-12 12:30:14',''),(71,'Long Term Care','long_term_care_planning','Long Term Care Fees',71,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can help you to protect your assets</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As people live longer, more and more of us face the possibility of going into residential care. This costs on average around &pound;450 per week which means that the money you worked so hard for all your life can soon be eaten away. There are ways to preserve your assets and that&rsquo;s where we can help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If your total assets (usually including the value of your home) exceed &pound;23,250&nbsp;&nbsp;then you will have to pay the care fees yourself, until your assets fall below that level (when the local authority will step in and contribute some of the cost). Certain assets are disregarded (see below) but the best way to prevent all your assets being used up by long term care fees is to come and see us at an early stage.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We specialise in Lifetime Planning &ndash; that is, we help people of all ages plan their future. We work closely with other professionals and the local authority to help people achieve their goals and to make sure there are no nasty surprises along the way.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So how can we make sure you hang on to your assets?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;&nbsp; NHS funding</strong><br />The NHS has to fund all or part of the cost of care in some circumstances. We can explain this in detail and liaise with the NHS funding authorities on your behalf.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>2.&nbsp; Make use of disregarded property</strong><br />Some types of assets are disregarded by the local authority when assessing your capital. This includes the value of your home if your partner, a relative over 60 or a relative under 60 who is mentally or physically disabled still lives there when you go into care. It also includes personal belongings, such as jewellery or cars. If you wish to rely on any property being disregarded it is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">vital</span> that you talk to us first, to make sure that it complies with the rules.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>3.&nbsp; Give away an asset</strong><br /><strong>WARNING: </strong>you cannot just give away an asset for these purposes. If you give something away and one of your reasons for doing so is to avoid care fees, the &ldquo;notional capital&rdquo; rules mean that you will be assessed as still owning that asset even after you give it away. You<strong> MUST</strong> see a solicitor before giving any assets away &ndash; however large or small. We can also tell you if there are any unforeseen tax or other implications of giving things away.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We recommend that you come to us as soon as you retire &ndash; or even earlier. We can then discuss giving assets away in the context of a long term plan. We can advise on types of trust available to you or alternatives to giving away the asset.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>4.&nbsp; Financial planning</strong><br />We work closely with independent financial advisers who specialise in long term care fees planning. There are many different products available, from bonds to insurance policies, which can help to preserve your assets. We would be happy to introduce you to a financial adviser and arrange a 3-way meeting with you, them and us. That way you know that your panel of experts are all working together in your best interests.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>5. Challenging funding decisions</strong><br />If you believe that the Local Authority&rsquo;s decision about the funding of your care is wrong then we can challenge it for you. We can help to ensure that the rules are followed correctly so that you don&rsquo;t pay more than you have to.</p>\r\nCall into one of our offices or telephone and we will be happy to arrange an initial appointment','2010-11-15 10:58:54','2011-11-29 15:33:13','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>We work with Independent Financial Advisors with specialist care planning&nbsp;qualifications.</p>\r\n<p>This ensures you get&nbsp;a complete package of advice.</p>\r\n<p>For a joint meeting call us today</p>','108_iStock_000013859617XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',98164,'2011-03-04 16:35:40','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','LongTermCare.jpg','image/jpeg',54456,'2010-12-22 10:09:58','Long-term Care Planning','','','Long-term Care Planning','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(72,'Residential Care Appeals','residential_care_appeals','Care Fee Appeals',72,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">You could be paying too much</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Did you know that if you or a relative need NURSING care, as opposed to PERSONAL care, then the care will paid for by the NHS? No means testing, no cost to you at all &ndash; no matter how much money you have,&nbsp;your care will be FREE.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Did you also know that if you or a relative have been wrongly assessed as having to pay for care then you can&nbsp;challenge it and may receive a rebate from the NHS? Sadly, many people are wrongly assessed and are asked to pay for their care when it should be free of charge. Is your relative one of them?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our specialist team are experienced in challenging care funding decisions and have successfully recovered thousands of pounds for our clients. If you believe you or a relative have been wrongly assessed then speak to us straight away.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You won&rsquo;t even have to pay us unless the challenge is successful.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 10:59:13','2011-11-29 15:33:42','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Have you reviewed your Will in the last five years?</p>\r\n<p>We can help even if your Will was not written by Banner Jones</p>','94_iStock_000009588868XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',47717,'2011-04-14 15:40:12','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','ResidentialCareAppeals.jpg','image/jpeg',55518,'2011-01-14 17:14:12','Residential Care Appeals','','','Residential Care Appeals','/web/contact_us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(74,'Retirement Planning','retirement_planning','Retirement Planning',74,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Planning for your future</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">We\'re with you every step of the way&hellip;</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As you approach retirement age you may want to start thinking about getting your financial affairs in order and making them as tax efficient as possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can advise you about everything from writing a tax efficient Will to setting up trusts for your Children.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We know there is alot to consider and you may not know where to start. With this in mind&nbsp;we have developed a <strong>Later Life Planning Consultation</strong> specifically for this purpose.&nbsp; In an hours private consultation you will be able to discuss your circumstances with an experienced solicitor who will then advise you on the best course of action to suit your needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the hour you can discuss things such as:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Wills and Trusts</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Inheritance Tax</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Care Fees Planning</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Lasting Powers of Attorney</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can even discuss funeral plans with you if required.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Following the consultation you will receive a comprehensive advice letter which will outline the recommended course of action for you.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please be reassured that there&nbsp;is&nbsp;no obligation to then undertake the work with Banner Jones.</p>','2010-11-15 10:59:57','2012-06-12 12:20:22','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>NEW</p>\r\n<p>Later Life Planning Consultation</p>\r\n<p>One hours private consultation with an experienced solicitor who will advise you on how to plan for your future</p>','75_iStock_000005717962XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',204931,'2011-11-29 14:30:27','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RetirementPlanning.jpg','image/jpeg',58385,'2011-01-11 11:53:19','Retirement Planning','','','Retirement Planning','','',NULL,'family_highlight','All of our Wills now include FREE registration&nbsp;','','','170_CertaintyNewLogo.JPG','image/jpeg',44954,'2012-06-12 12:20:22',''),(75,'Defence Representation','derence_representation','Defence Representation',75,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','','2010-11-15 11:00:20','2011-01-21 15:40:46','','',1,1,0,NULL,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DefenceRepresentation.jpg','image/jpeg',42487,'2010-12-22 09:41:54','Defence Representation','','','Defence Representation','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(76,'Road Traffic Offences','road_traffic_offences','Caught by a speed camera?',76,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With ever advancing technology constantly monitoring our driving, more and more people are finding themselves charged with Road Traffic Offences. Whether it&rsquo;s exceeding the speed limit or one of the many other offences, they all attract penalties which can quite often&nbsp; lead to significant fines, the endorsement of points on driving licences and ultimately the loss of a licence.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For some people losing their licence may mean losing their job and have other disastrous consequences. Our specialist Motoring Law Team are experienced in defending or mitigating charges and penalties, often with the result that a driving ban is avoided.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our specialist Motoring Law team can provide advice and guidance in all motoring matters including:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Speeding offences</li>\r\n<li>Driving under the influence of drugs and or alcohol</li>\r\n<li>Dangerous and careless driving</li>\r\n<li>Failing to comply with traffic signals</li>\r\n<li>Defective vehicles</li>\r\n<li>Driving without insurance</li>\r\n<li>Driving whilst disqualified</li>\r\n<li>Using mobile phones</li>\r\n<li>Failing to provide information/stop after an accident</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you need fast, reliable and professional advice on how to defend a Road Traffic charge and perhaps avoid conviction or disqualification please contact us. There are instances where challenges can be made but it is crucial that you take legal advice before taking any other action.','2010-11-15 11:00:39','2011-04-14 15:57:04','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>If you have received a speeding fine, contact us to see if we can help you</p>','107_iStock_000013404152XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',42987,'2011-04-14 15:57:04','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RoadTrafficOffences.jpg','image/jpeg',35581,'2010-12-22 10:13:37','Road Traffic Offences','','','Road Traffic Offences','/web/contact_us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(77,'Public Order Offences','public_order_offences','Public Order Offences',77,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','TEXT NEEDED or we hide the page?','2010-11-15 11:00:54','2011-03-01 15:42:54','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','PublicOrderOffences.jpg','image/jpeg',44778,'2010-12-22 10:12:16','Public Order Offences','','','Public Order Offences','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(78,'Civil Liberties','civil_liberty_ottences','Civil Liberties',78,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','text needed or we hide the page','2010-11-15 11:01:17','2011-03-01 15:43:40','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','CivilLiberties.jpg','image/jpeg',50960,'2010-12-22 09:39:31','Civil Liberty','','','Civil Liberty','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(79,'Dispute Resolution','dispute_resolution__family','Dispute resolution',79,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Is a dispute giving you a headache?</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">We\'re with you every step of the way...</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The types of disputes we see on a day to day basis are extremely varied, but we know that every client who comes to see has the same question on their mind &ndash; do I have a case?&nbsp; Our team of experts will help and guide you through your case and let you know the likely outcome from the start.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We recognise the importance of keeping dispute cases out of court so wherever possible we will always avoid litigation, but if required we will fight fearlessly for your rights.</p>\r\nIf you think you have a dispute case and want to have a chat with a specialist solicitor please contact us.','2010-11-15 11:03:37','2011-11-29 14:46:43','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Are you a private landlord with several properties?</p>\r\n<p>Had problems with rent collection and evictions?</p>\r\n<p>Let us help you</p>','105_iStock_000013135809XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',249179,'2011-03-04 16:39:03','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DisputeResolution.jpg','image/jpeg',50597,'2010-12-22 09:43:32','Dispute Resolution','','','Dispute Resolution','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(80,'Employment Law','employment_disputes','Employment Law',80,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Problems at work?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Employment law changes more rapidly than any other area of the law, which is why if you think you have an issue it&rsquo;s best to seek advice as soon as possible.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re here to put your mind at ease and make sure that your rights as an employee are withheld. If you have an employment problem, quite often there maybe something else for consideration within your case so it&rsquo;s always worth finding out for certain.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can advise you on the legal rights to which you are entitled &ndash; whether they relate to disciplinary proceedings, maternity rights, discrimination, redundancy, applications to Employment Tribunals, or any other disputes.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Often the right advice at the right time can lead to matters being resolved with the minimum of stress to you.</p>','2010-11-15 11:04:16','2011-11-29 14:43:22','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>New Paternity rights April 2011</p>\r\n<p>For a&nbsp;summary click here</p>','34_Family Image.jpg','image/jpeg',276475,'2011-02-28 14:57:13','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','EmploymentDisputes.jpg','image/jpeg',51721,'2010-12-22 09:44:02','Employment Disputes','','','Employment Disputes','/page/maternity-and-paternity-rights','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(81,'Consumer Disputes','consumer_disputes__dispute_resolution','Problem with a faulty product?',81,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have a problem with goods you have purchased, we may be able to negotiate a satisfactory resolution. If necessary, we will act for you in enforcing your rights through the courts.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our experience covers many types of dispute. Typical examples are:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>faulty cars and other goods which are not satisfactory</li>\r\n<li>hire purchase and credit agreements for unsatisfactory goods</li>\r\n<li>faulty or incomplete work by builders or other tradesmen</li>\r\n<li>unfair consumer contracts</li>\r\n<li>holidays that do not match their description in a brochure</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 11:04:55','2011-03-24 16:44:22','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Do you know what your rights are?</p>\r\n<p>Click here for a full list of consumer rights</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','52_iStock_000000751879XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',147335,'2011-03-04 16:40:23','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','ConsumerDisputes.jpg','image/jpeg',51918,'2011-01-12 14:30:04','Consumer Disputes','','','Consumer Disputes','','http://www.consumerdirect.gov.uk/after_you_buy/know-your-rights/',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(82,'Property Disputes','property_disputes','Problem with a boundary?',82,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Property disputes can be very stressful as they often arise when a building job has not been completed properly or maybe you are rowing with a neighbour over a boundary fence?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our expertise in the complex area of building disputes applies a sound commercial approach to achieving a resolution whether you are an individual, or a construction company.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Starting with the contract you entered into, we identify the essential elements of the dispute.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can&nbsp; help you with claims concerning:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Failure to carry out or complete building work</li>\r\n<li>Defective construction</li>\r\n<li>Disputes over costs</li>\r\n<li>Boundary disputes on your land</li>\r\n<li>Ownership disputes </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can act either in the defence of the building company, or for individuals and businesses that are in dispute with builders</p>\r\nWe can also advise you in creating a professional contract with a builder at the start of a job so that if things turn bad you have a legally binding contract to fall back on.','2010-11-15 11:05:28','2011-03-24 16:48:42','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Planning an extension?&nbsp; Get a legally binding contract in place with your builder.</p>\r\n<p>It\'s better to be safe than sorry</p>','60_iStock_000001722438XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',93059,'2011-03-24 16:47:37','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','PropertyDisputes.jpg','image/jpeg',44851,'2010-12-22 10:11:43','Property Disputes','','','Property Disputes','/page/contact-us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(83,'Landlord/Tenant Disputes','land_lord_or_tenant_disputes','Frustrated with bad tenants?',83,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>If you are a landord of private residential property then you may be suffering with bad tenants.</p>\r\n<p>Our expert dispute resolution team&nbsp;can advise on the problems of either landlords or tenants. We combine our knowledge of this specialised area of law with practical advice.</p>\r\n<h2>Landlords</h2>\r\n<p>Typical problems on which we advise are breaches of tenancy agreements and rent arrears. We can act for you in obtaining possession of your property &ndash; processing the matter from the initial notice to eviction if necessary.</p>\r\n<p>Our new <strong>FIXED FEE Landlord Assist</strong>&nbsp;scheme will help you be able to budget as you will know the exact cost at the start of the proceedings.&nbsp; With prices starting from &pound;140 +vat&nbsp; contact us now for more information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Tenants</h2>\r\n<p>If the property you rent is in disrepair, or you are suffering harassment or unlawful eviction, we can advise you on your rights and take legal action against your landlord where appropriate.</p>','2010-11-15 11:06:08','2011-03-28 14:16:38','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Ease your stress with our New</p>\r\n<p>Fixed Fee Landlord Assist package</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','105_iStock_000013135809XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',249179,'2011-03-04 16:42:07','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','LandlordDisputes.jpg','image/jpeg',65876,'2010-12-22 17:12:06','Landlord/Tenant Disputes','','','Landlord/Tenant Disputes','/page/contact-us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(84,'Wills, Trusts and Estate Disputes','wills_trusts_and_estate_disputes','We\'ll help you get your rightful share',84,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Wills by there very nature can be contentious and often certain family members who have been neglected in the Will may wish to challenge the other beneficiaries to get what they believe is their rightful share.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you would like more information about contesting a Will, we can tell you the sorts of things that can be looked at in ruling a Will invalid.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It can be a very lengthy and drawn out process so we always advise that families think carefully about this before taking such action to avoid irriversible rifts in the family.</p>','2010-11-15 11:06:46','2011-05-17 15:20:09','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>To avoid this happening to your family, make sure your Will is up to date and provides for everyone you want it to</p>\r\n<p>Review your Will now</p>','49_wom with baby.JPG','image/jpeg',185944,'2011-03-01 14:52:39','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','WillsTrustsAndEstateDisputes.jpg','image/jpeg',54254,'2011-01-13 14:56:52','Wills, Trusts and Estate disputes','','','Wills, Trusts and Estate disputes','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(85,'Debt Recovery','debt_recovery__family','Debt Recovery ',85,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Need to recover a debt? We can help you</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sometimes a letter from a solicitor is all it takes ...</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you have a problem collecting money owed to you, we have the expertise to help . We will pursue your debts as quickly as possible in a cost-effective way, combining our knowledge and experience with our specialist case management software.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If the debtor does not pay the debt quickly, we will consult you on how far to pursue it and whether to litigate. If a court order is obtained and the debtor still fails to pay, we will enforce payment by the most appropriate means. Throughout the process, we will keep you informed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In some cases it is appropriate to consider bankruptcy proceedings against an individual, or winding-up proceedings if the debtor is a company. We will discuss these options with you.</p>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our Fixed Fee debt collection&nbsp;service is a really cost effective way for you to collect debts owing to you</h1>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Stage 1</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Send a Solicitors Letter before action and report on response at no initial cost to you.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &pound;0.00*</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">*or 5% of sum recovered (up to &pound;2,500) if