 width=\"250\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p>Sheriff Enforcement (Debt over &pound;600)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"91\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p>&pound;30.00</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"133\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p>&pound;50.00</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"94\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p>&pound;80.00</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><sub>Any additional correspondence between the parties is chargeable at current charging rates. If a Defence is received the matter can be passed to our Dispute Resolution Department who will advise of possible costs and charging rates.</sub></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><sub>* Please be aware that although every effort is made, we cannot guarantee recovery of your claim. Once litigation action has been instigated you will be liable to discharge all Legal fees whether we are successful or not. In the instance recovery is obtained from the debtor, the Legal fees recovered will duly be credited to you.</sub></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><sub>** Alternative enforcement procedures are available and advice and costings can be supplied on request.</sub></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 11:07:58','2011-11-29 14:47:27','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<h3>Fixed Fee Debt Recovery Service</h3>\r\n<p>contact us today</p>','83_iStock_000007854419XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',99712,'2011-03-04 16:43:11','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','DebtRecovery.jpg','image/jpeg',55974,'2010-12-22 09:41:23','Debt Recovery','','','Debt Recovery','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(86,'Notary','notary_services__family','Notary in Chesterfield',86,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We provide a fast and efficient Notary Public service in Chesterfield&nbsp;at competitive rates. Whether you are a business engaged in international trade or you wish to be married outside the UK, we provide a comprehensive, high quality service.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What is a Notary Public?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A Notary is a qualified lawyer with a specialist additional qualification, appointed by the Archbishop of Canterbury. The rules which affect Notaries are very similar to the rules which affect Solicitors.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What can a Notary do?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A Notary&rsquo;s work normally involves the preparation and authentication of documents for use abroad, Notaries are recognised internationally, unlike Solicitors.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many notaries do work for commercial firms engaged in international trade, and for private individuals. The most common tasks are:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Dealing with documents for weddings abroad</li>\r\n<li>Preparing and witnessing powers of attorney for use overseas </li>\r\n<li>Dealing with purchase or sale of land and property abroad </li>\r\n<li>Providing documents to deal with the administration of the estate of people who are abroad, or owning property abroad </li>\r\n<li>Authenticating personal documents and information for immigration or emigration purposes, or to work abroad </li>\r\n<li>Authenticating company and business documents and transactions</li>\r\n<li>Notarising medical reports and police reports&nbsp;for use in connection with accidents abroad</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Preparing to see a Notary</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although every case will be different, you will need to ensure:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>You make an appointment</li>\r\n<li>You bring evidence of your identity to the appointment, such as a current valid passport and/or driving licence and a recent utlity bill or bank statement with your name and address on it</li>\r\n<li>You understand any documents involved, particularly if it is not in English</li>\r\n<li>You bring any documents to the appointment that are relevant to the matter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Please <a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/12_VISITING  A NOTARY PUBLIC NOTES FOR CLIENTS.doc?1311348870\" target=\"_blank\">read this guide</a> before coming to see Stephen Gordon, our Notary in Chesterfield.</h2>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What is the cost?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The fee will be based upon the amount of time that is spent dealing with your matter, however a quotation will be provided in advance.&nbsp; All quotes are subject to VAT.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you would like to make an appointment or for further information, please contact Stephen Gordon on 01246 560560 or <a href=\"mailto:sg@bannerjones.co.uk?\">sg@bannerjones.co.uk</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Regulation</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Notaries are regluated in England and Wales by the Faculty Office of the Archbishop of Canterbury of The Sanctuary, Westminster, London, SW1P 3JT</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Professional Indemnity Insurance</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our Notary is covered by Banner Jones Solicitors Professional Indemnity Insurance.&nbsp;&nbsp; The Professional Rules for Notaries can be accessed either on the&nbsp; <a href=\"http://www.facultyoffice.org.uk\" target=\"_blank\">Faculty Office website</a>&nbsp;or the <a href=\"http://www.thenotariessociety.org.uk\" target=\"_blank\">Notarial services website</a>.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Complaints Procedure</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The vast majority of our clients are totally satisfied with the Notarial service we provide, however, in order to comply with the Notaries\' Code of Practice, we need to advise you of what to do should you become unhappy with our service.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If at any time there is anything concerning you about the progress of your matter, you should contact the Notary dealing with your case, who will&nbsp; try to deal with your concern.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If your concern is not dealt with in this way you can persue a complaint under the Notaries Approved Complaints Procedure by contacting the Secretary of the Notaries Society of Old Church Chambers, 23 Sandhill Road, St. James, Northampton, NN5 5LH.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Any matters not resolved by the Notaries Society\'s Approved Complaints Procedure will be dealt with by the Office for Legal Complaints at the Court of Faculties.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','2010-11-15 11:08:57','2011-09-26 15:12:17','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Stephen Gordon</p>\r\n<p>Notary Public</p>\r\n<p>Chesterfield</p>','Stephen.jpg','image/pjpeg',80854,'2011-03-01 15:49:13','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Notary.jpg','image/jpeg',31220,'2010-12-22 10:10:26','Notary','','','Notary','/team_members/39','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(87,'What our clients say...','testimonials','Testimonials',87,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42',NULL,'2010-11-15 13:49:30','2011-02-16 15:41:10','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(89,'Offices','offices','Offices',89,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','','2010-11-16 13:08:18','2010-12-09 12:28:53','','',1,1,0,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(90,'Pay Online','pay_online','Pay Online',90,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','','2010-11-16 13:10:21','2011-03-28 13:56:30','','',1,1,0,NULL,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(91,'Case Studies','case_studies','Case Studies',91,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42',NULL,'2010-11-18 13:47:02','2010-11-18 13:47:09','','',1,1,0,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(92,'Slander','defarmation_and_slander','Slander',92,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>In recent months we have a rise in slander cases. This means that someone believes something bad has been said against them and they want to fight to clear their name.</p>','2010-12-08 13:57:06','2011-01-21 15:42:18','','',1,1,0,NULL,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Slander.jpg','image/jpeg',36578,'2010-12-22 10:16:20','Defamation and Slander','','','Defamation and Slander','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(93,'Collaborative Law','collaborative_law','Keeping you out of court',93,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Collaborative Family Law offers you a fresh approach to how family breakdown is dealt with and rather than dealing through solicitors, you work with them to find a solution best for you and your family.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A satisfied client told us;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&ldquo;I found the process as amicable as could have been expected and would recommend it where there are children involved as it appears to have had minimal effect on my son. The extra time involved was well worth it in order to maintain a civil relationship with my wife during this period&rdquo;&nbsp; - Mr. L, Sheffield.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">How is Collaborative Law different?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Couples who work Collaboratively sign an agreement not to go to court but to meet face to face to discuss reaching a fair and balanced outcome. The benefit of a non-court based process is it allows you;</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>To control the pace, timescale and outcome of your discussions</li>\r\n<li>To find a solution bespoke to your own circumstances</li>\r\n<li>To give careful consideration to&nbsp;complicated business, family business or high value investment interests</li>\r\n<li>To work with other specialist advisers such as accountants, financial advisers and pension experts jointly with your partner if required</li>\r\n<li>To keep things as amicable as possible (which is particularly important where there are children involved)</li>\r\n<li>To avoid conflict and deal with your seperation in a dignified manner</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>What is involved?<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The process is based upon each party having their own Collaboratively trained lawyer. Progress is made in a series of four-way meetings, face to face, sat round the table. There are no letters or phone calls except to arrange the meetings and to circulate the minutes of those meetings. Both parties and their Collaborative lawyers as well as making a commitment not to go to court, agree to a set of basic ground rules. Negotiations are based upon full financial disclosure, and when needed, other jointly instructed neutral professionals (such as accountants) can be brought in to assist in the process. Solutions are based upon the parties&rsquo; interests and needs rather than conflicting positions. Sometimes only a couple of meetings are needed, sometimes four or five. These meetings can be close together or widely spaced depending upon your individual circumstances. The choice is yours. Once agreement is reached, your Collaborative lawyer will make it binding for you and put the agreement into effect. For couples and families who genuinely seek a fair solution and want to mimimise the pain of family breakdown, Collaborative Law may offer the best approach.</p>','2010-12-08 14:04:52','2011-04-20 14:45:44','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Click here for more information on Collaborative Law</p>','3_CollaborativeLaw.jpg','image/jpeg',19022,'2011-01-21 16:30:33','Collaborative Law','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','CollaborativeLaw.jpg','image/jpeg',52522,'2011-01-13 16:16:41','Collaborative Law','','','Collaborative Law','','http://www.resolution.org.uk/editorial.asp?page_id=53',5,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(94,'Mediation','mediation','Cotton Mediation',94,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you want to divorce or separate from your Partner, there will be many issues that arise and need resolving. Our Mediation service, Cotton Mediation can help you resolve these issues. Meeting with an impartial Mediator means you can discuss and agree solutions in a friendly, neutral setting away from the pressures and strain of court proceedings.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Mediation can help you make decisions about:</strong></p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li><strong></strong>Arrangements for the care of your children</li>\r\n<li><strong></strong>Financial arrangements</li>\r\n<li><strong></strong>Dividing up your property and other shared assets</li>\r\n<li><strong></strong>Your separation or divorce</li>\r\n<li><strong></strong>How you and your Partner will communicate in future</li>\r\n<li><strong></strong>Any other related issues</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our specialist Mediators are experienced in dealing with complicated situations and helping clients find the best solutions in the interests of the whole family.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We also work closely with other professionals such as local Solicitors, Financial Advisors and Accountants as well as other experienced local Mediators. This way we can offer a comprehensive service to our clients. Mediation is available to anyone whether you are married or not, have children or not.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The first meeting is free so why not come and find out more about how Cotton Mediation can help. &nbsp;You may find you are also eligible for public funding.</p>','2010-12-08 14:13:44','2011-12-01 15:32:05','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Do you think Mediation could help?</p>\r\n<p>Ask us about our Mediation service today</p>','148_Cotton Medation Logo_FINAL.JPG','image/jpeg',42544,'2011-12-01 15:32:05',NULL,'family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Mediation.jpg','image/jpeg',55083,'2011-01-13 14:52:33','Mediation','','','Mediation','','',NULL,'family_highlight','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(95,'Property Matters','property_matters','Property Ownership',95,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Believe it or not the way you own your property is very important if you want to leave a share of it to somebody in your Will. For example:</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Owning as \"Joint Tenants\"</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This way, neither of you owns an identifiable share of the property. You collectively own the whole thing - essentially you hold it on trust for yourselves. This means that when one of you dies, the property automatically passes to the survivor(s). It does not matter whether or not the deceased co-owner had a Will.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Owning as \"Tenants in Common\"</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">By owning this way, you each own an identifiable share of the property. Unless you have stated otherwise, this will be 50% each for 2 owners or one third each for 3 owners etc. You are each free to use your share in any way you want. You can give it away during your lifetime, or can leave it to someone under your Will. Owning as Tenants in Common, the property will not automatically pass to the surviving owner(s) so it is <em>vital</em> that you each have a Will.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Why is it important to own the right way?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You MUST own the property as Tenants in Common if you want to:-</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Give your share to someone else</li>\r\n<li>Leave your share under your Will</li>\r\n<li>Put your share into trust for someone else&rsquo;s benefit</li>\r\n<li>Engage in any inheritance tax planning</li>\r\n<li>Plan for future care fees</li>\r\n<li>Have extra flexibility in dealing with your assets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you don&rsquo;t know how your current property is&nbsp;owned, &nbsp;the chances are you own as joint tenants. However, we can easily check this for you. All we need is to see your title deeds.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is very simple to change from joint tenants to tenants in common. We would be happy to prepare the necessary paperwork and register the change at HM Land Registry on your behalf.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you are Tenants in Common already and want to change the share of the property that you each own, this can be done easily and we can provide an estimate of cost for you.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Equity Release Schemes</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are various schemes which allow you to release some of the value (&ldquo;equity&rdquo;) that is locked into your home.&nbsp; To find out more <a href=\"../../../page/equity-release\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a></p>','2010-12-08 15:52:34','2011-11-29 15:32:34','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Worried about how you\'ll pay for&nbsp;Care Home fees?&nbsp;&nbsp; Do Not sell your home before speaking to us first</p>','care homes cropped.JPG','image/pjpeg',169229,'2011-03-01 10:23:16','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','PropertyMatters.jpg','image/jpeg',63973,'2011-01-11 11:52:51','Property Matters','','','Property Matters','/page/services-for-the-elderly','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(96,'Lasting Power of Attorney','lasting_power_of_attorney','Lasting Power of Attorney',96,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Thinking about the unthinkable</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A Lasting Power of Attorney (LPA) &nbsp;is created to allow someone else the ability to look after your affairs if your mental capacity is lost. It isn\'t a nice thing to think about which is why most people will put it off as long as they can.&nbsp;&nbsp; We would advise however,&nbsp;that you do this sooner rather than later as an LPA can only be created when your&nbsp;mental capacity is&nbsp;sound.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">More often than not people create Lasting Powers of Attorney in later life when there is a higher chance of mental capacity being lost through dementia for example.&nbsp; However, mental capacity can be lost at any age as a result of say, an accident so we would also advise anyone with complex financial affairs to have one as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At Banner Jones we can advise you on the best course of action for your particular circumstances.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What do I do next?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are always keen to find the best solution possible for your particular circumstances, and we know that no two families are the same. Whatever your circumstances you can telephone us or make an appointment to discuss your situation with us in more detail. We will then be able advise you as to the best way forward.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Why not&nbsp;&nbsp;read our&nbsp;<a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/13_Factsheet - Lasting Power of Attorney.docx?1322579386\" target=\"_blank\">free guide</a> to LPA\'s&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','2010-12-08 16:05:58','2012-01-20 12:18:11','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Click here for more FREE information on powers of attorney</p>','153_The-Law-Donut.jpg','image/jpeg',56338,'2012-01-20 12:18:11',NULL,'family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','LastingPowerOfAttorney.jpg','image/jpeg',52132,'2010-12-23 12:27:03','Lasting Power of Attorney','','','Lasting Power of Attorney','','http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/personal-law/powers-of-attorney/?s=BAN082',NULL,'family_highlight','','/page/notary-family','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(97,'Starting a Business','starting_a_business','Starting a Business',97,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>Got lots of questions?</h2>\r\n<p>Starting a business is an exciting time but there are several things you&rsquo;ll need to consider and our team of experts are here to help you every step of the way.</p>\r\n<p>You may be uncertain about how to structure you business, how to finance it, whether to employ staff or whether to rent or buy commercial property. It is important to seek the right legal advice at the start because if your foundations are not right then the business will have problems growing.</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/starting-up/?s=BAN082\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;Click&nbsp;here access our &nbsp;additional resources for businesses</p>\r\n</a><img src=\"../../..//assets/page_contents/97/contained_images/def9a0ec09d4_153_The-Law-Donut.jpg?1326295165\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"193\" height=\"59\" />','2010-12-09 08:48:06','2012-01-20 11:17:26','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>GIVE YOUR NEW BUSINESS SOME TLC</p>\r\n<p>LEGAL PROTECTION AT A FIXED MONTHLY COST</p>','110_tlc.JPG','image/jpeg',18257,'2011-03-29 14:41:33','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','StartingABusiness.jpg','image/jpeg',46316,'2010-12-22 09:29:46','Starting a Business','','','Starting a Business','/page/total-legal-care-insurance','',NULL,'family_highlight','','/page/total-legal-care-insurance','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(98,'Running a Business','running_a_business','Running a Business',98,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>Time to review?</h2>\r\n<p>Running a business can be extremely stressful so it&rsquo;s important to have the right partners in place to ensure your business stays on track. As your legal partner we will give you as much or as little advice as you need, but be assured we&rsquo;ll be with you every step of the way. We can advise you on everything from the renewal of staff contracts through to helping you claim for any unpaid debts.</p>\r\n<p>Why not let us take some of the stress away by having your own dedicated commercial lawyer on tap?&nbsp; With a fixed cost monthly retainer from <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"../../../page/total-legal-care-insurance\">Total Legal Care</a></span>, we&rsquo;ll give you business and employment law advice whenever you need it at no additional cost.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2010-12-09 09:12:58','2012-01-20 11:29:09','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Would you like some advice on Data Protection and IT issues?</p>\r\n<p>Click here for more information</p>','153_The-Law-Donut.jpg','image/jpeg',56338,'2012-01-20 11:28:09','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','RunningABusiness.jpg','image/jpeg',45684,'2011-01-13 14:43:19','Running a Business','','','Running a Business','','http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/data-protection-and-it/?s=BAN082',NULL,'family_highlight','','/page/total-legal-care-insurance','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(99,'Exiting a Business','exiting_a_business','Business Exit Strategies',99,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Time to get out?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Exiting a business can be extremely emotional&nbsp;so it&rsquo;s important to have the right partners in place guide you through the process.&nbsp;&nbsp; As your legal partner we will give you as much or as little advice as you need, but be assured we&rsquo;ll be with you every step of the way.&nbsp;&nbsp; We can advise you on everything from selling your business premises to raise capital through to full liquidation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Why not let us take some of the stress away by having your own dedicated commercial lawyer on tap?&nbsp; With a fixed cost monthly retainer from <a href=\"../../../page/total-legal-care-insurance\">Total Legal Care</a>, we&rsquo;ll give you business and employment law advice whenever you need it at no additional cost.</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/exit-strategies/?s=BAN082\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For more information on company exit strategies please click here</p>\r\n</a><img src=\"../../..//assets/page_contents/99/contained_images/2c4c0363a35f_153_The-Law-Donut.jpg?1326295165\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"200\" height=\"57\" />','2010-12-09 09:56:41','2012-01-20 11:52:21','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'If you need assitance selling your business premises we can help','77_iStock_000005896679XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',115487,'2011-03-04 10:57:28','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','ExitingABusiness.jpg','image/jpeg',45758,'2010-12-22 09:27:59','Exiting a Business','','','Exiting a Business','','',NULL,'family_highlight','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(100,'Succession Planning','succession','Passing it on',100,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Succession is the Transfer of ownership and/or management<strong> </strong>of the business to the next generation.&nbsp; As a business grows, over the years a generation gap will more than likely appear.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Typically the 1<sup>st</sup> generation will be one or more close family members, often of a similar age.&nbsp; The 2<sup>nd</sup> generation will be their children and the 3<sup>rd</sup> generation could be the cousins, possibly with a wide range of ages and the family ties not as close as siblings so overall the ownership becomes more fragmented.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Gift of Business</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Some owners come under pressure from the next generation who think that it is their &ldquo;right&rdquo; to be given the business, but in some cases such a Gift may mean that the current generation of owners do not have sufficient funds to retire.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are many questions about surrounding gifting the business, such as:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Who do you give shares to?</li>\r\n<li>Do you treat all children equally?</li>\r\n<li>Does fairly mean equally?</li>\r\n<li>What about those who are not involved in the business now?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Are you a custodian for the next generation?</li>\r\n<li>Should you expect to gift the business on? </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can help you with the answers to these questions.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sale of Business</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Selling the business provides the opportunity for the current generation to realise the value and have the funds to retire. It also provides opportunity for the current generation to share proceeds with family members who are not participating in next generation.&nbsp; But how do you agree a fair price? What is affordable? It could open up the opportunity for other non-family management to participate in ownership i.e. a Management Buy Out.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Gradual handover</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When the current generation of owners accept that it is time to step back, for some businesses a more gradual handover may be appropriate. A gradual handover allows the current owners to be paid out over time which maybe better for the business financially and it also gives chance for younger family members to start getting involved in the business.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You might also consider a transfer of management before ownership. This would allow a balance between outright transfer and retaining some management control. You might want to ensure the next generation have the capability to run the business before handing it over and losing control altogether.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can advise you and help you understand when voting control has transferred on a gradual handover.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Other things to consider in Succession planning</h2>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Every adult should have a Will &ndash; if you own a business then this is essential to plan for unexpected events. If there are minor children involved then consider if the business can continue to be run by trustees in the future?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A Will is vital if ownership is being transferred gradually.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">IHT advice is also an important of planning.</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Articles of Association. These may include Shareholders Agreements, Partnership Agreements and Family Charters.&nbsp; All businesses should consider having an agreement regulating their conduct, family businesses are no different but they also have the option of a family charter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Review Property Ownership. Who owns the business property?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Can the business property be treated as separate to the main business?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This may provide opportunities for family members to acquire/inherit the property rather than the main business. Is there a lease in place?&nbsp; Should there be a lease?</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Divorce: If your children own a share of the family business &ndash; will this result in assets being lost in divorce proceedings? Does it discourage transfer of ownership?&nbsp; Will there be a possibility of the business having to help fund a divorce settlement? <a href=\"../../../page/collaborative-law\">Collaborative law</a> would be a recommended route for a family business where conflict resolution is required</li>\r\n</ul>','2010-12-10 16:28:54','2011-03-30 11:22:50','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>We can involve an Independent Financial Adviser in our discussions at no extra cost to you</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','77_iStock_000005896679XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',115487,'2011-03-04 11:47:26','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','SuccessionPlanning.jpg','image/jpeg',51694,'2010-12-22 09:30:19','Succession','','','Succession','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(101,'Family Charters','family_charter','Setting the groundrules',101,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We would recommend that any &nbsp;family business considers entering into a Family Charter.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Family Charter (sometimes called Family Constitutions or Protocols) are statements of intent or agreements entered into by the family members in relation to the family business. A Family Charter is a formal&nbsp;agreement between family members regulating their conduct in respect of the family business and although not normally legally binding, parts can be legally binding if this is required by the family.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Family Charter would normally set out confirmation of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>How the family want the business to be run</li>\r\n<li>The goals and long term planning and strategy for the business</li>\r\n<li>The family members&rsquo; different relationships with the business</li>\r\n<li>How the family members should behave towards each other in the context of the business</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We find that, rather like entering into a Shareholders&rsquo; Agreement, the process of working through the various elements of the Family Charter is, in itself, a very important and positive exercise for a family business to undertake.&nbsp; The Family Charter can be a route map for both the business and the family moving forward.&nbsp; It can also be a way of reaching an overall agreement on how a number of issues should be addressed in the future.&nbsp; These issues can be whatever the family members think are relevant, but could cover:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Future employment for the Directors of the business.&nbsp; Should these be from within the family or external Directors?</li>\r\n<li>Who should be employed in the business?</li>\r\n<li>What happens if somebody wants to sell their shares?</li>\r\n<li>Should all family members be entitled to own shares regardless of their involvement in the business?</li>\r\n<li>Should spouses and in-laws be entitled to own shares?</li>\r\n<li>What happens if there is dispute between family members in relation to the business?</li>\r\n<li>How does the family tackle a difference of views as to why the family are in business together or which direction the business should take?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The above list is not an exhaustive list and the things to be considered by each family business in the Family Charter will be unique to them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The benefit to the business can be significant.&nbsp; We would also recommend that businesses that have a Charter should look to review and amend it on a regular basis to ensure that the route map is still the right direction for the business and the direction that the family members continue to wish the business to take.</p>\r\n<p>Please feel free to contact any member of the Family Business Team to discuss the benefits that a Family Charter can bring to your business.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2010-12-10 16:32:42','2011-07-29 08:17:42','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>As a Family business owner a Will is essential.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Call us now to make your appointment</p>','99_iStock_000011161195XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',202161,'2011-03-30 11:24:55','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','FamilyCharters.jpg','image/jpeg',31732,'2010-12-22 09:29:00','Family Charter','','','Family Charter','/page/making-a-will','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(102,'Remuneration','remuneration','Money, money, money',102,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are different types of remuneration that can be considered including salaries for working employees and bonuses or dividends for owners.&nbsp;&nbsp; The big question we hear is often about how much to pay. It is often hard to balance between a fair salary for active and non-active members of the family.&nbsp; We hear stories about families working hard to pay dividends to siblings who don&rsquo;t contribute to the business.&nbsp; We also hear about family members receiving a higher than market rate salary so as to ensure a comfortable lifestyle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Taxation</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We often see tax inefficiencies from owners who would rather be paid a larger salary to avoid sharing dividends with siblings.&nbsp; All this does is simply result in a larger tax bill.&nbsp; Beware of paying a &ldquo;salary&rdquo; to a family member who doesn&rsquo;t work &ndash; the Inland Revenue will&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Employee rights &ndash; suing your children/parents for unfair dismissal</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Outsiders</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You need to pay the market rate for new recruits, particularly if at a senior level who have little prospect of ever becoming owners.&nbsp; You should also be aware of the potential conflict between higher paid family members in more junior roles. This can be quite frustrating for non-family employees who work just as hard as the family member.&nbsp;&nbsp; A formal bonus scheme might be a way to equal out the remuneration among all staff.</p>','2010-12-10 16:35:52','2011-03-04 11:57:44','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>We can involve Independent Financial Advisers in our discussions at no extra cost to you</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','77_iStock_000005896679XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',115487,'2011-03-04 11:57:44','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Remuneration.jpg','image/jpeg',36392,'2010-12-22 09:29:25','Remuneration','','','Remuneration','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(103,'Commercial Insolvency','commercial_insolvency','Commerical Insolvency',103,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">You are not on your own</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is a tragic inevitability that during 2011/12 many businesses will experience financial difficulties. Often these impact not only on the trading position of the business itself but also on the lives of the business owners.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At Banner Jones, we have the benefit of many years of experience in dealing with business turnaround and insolvency. We will look for the most effective rescue package for the business to enable it to go forwards either to be sold or run by a newly invigorated owner.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The solutions we are able to offer are available to all types of business including individuals trading in person as well as limited companies.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our solutions include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Full scale Insolvencies including <a href=\"../../../page/company-voluntary-arrangements\">Company Voluntary Arrangements</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Liquidation</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Partnership and <a href=\"../../../page/individual-voluntary-arrangements\">Individual Voluntary Arrangements</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Debt negotiation and dispute resolution</li>\r\n</ul>','2010-12-17 16:25:23','2011-11-29 14:52:06','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>If your relationship has suffered and you need some advice</p>\r\n<p>We can help</p>','65_iStock_000002761784XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',140936,'2011-03-04 11:01:05','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','CommercialInsolvency.jpg','image/jpeg',49266,'2011-01-12 13:36:48','Commercial Insolvency','','','Commercial Insolvency','/page/divorce-and-separation','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(104,'Company Voluntary Arrangements','company_voluntary_arrangements','Company Voluntary Arrangements',104,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span>This is a process where a proposal is put to the company&rsquo;s creditors and if 75% of the value of those who vote are in favour of the proposal then all of the company&rsquo;s unsecured debt is rolled into the arrangement. Normally the company will then pay a monthly amount for a period of 5 years to satisfy the debt in full. More often than not the total amount paid is less than the total amount owed.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span>This can be a very effective solution and avoids the company going into any form of liquidation. Therefore it continues as a going concern and its trading position need not be effected.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span>Often the voluntary arrangement includes the appointment of a company Administrator and therefore often people associate this process with Administration.</span></p>','2010-12-17 16:26:56','2011-03-30 11:05:21','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Don\'t forget to update your Will whenever your circumstances change</p>\r\n<p>We can help you do this</p>','51_iStock_000000217478XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',168473,'2011-03-30 11:05:21','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','CompanyVoluntaryArrangements.jpg','image/jpeg',47510,'2011-01-13 14:40:33','Company Voluntary Arrangements','','','Company Voluntary Arrangements','/page/contact-us','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(107,'Individual Voluntary Arrangements','individual_voluntary_arrangements','Individual Voluntary Arrangements',107,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span>Partnership/Individual Voluntary Arrangements</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span>Where debt is held personally rather than in a limited company name it can be more troublesome. This is principally for the reason that the personal assets of the business owner, including their home, can be under threat. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span>A partnership voluntary arrangement is used where there are more than one business owners trading in partnership and an individual voluntary arrangement is used for one person alone. Equally a series of individual voluntary arrangements can be used and this can often be the case in relation to either business partners or other partners. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span>In the same way as a company voluntary arrangement 75% of the value of those who vote need to vote in favour of any proposal. Most proposals again involve monthly payments over a 5 year period after which time the debt is discharged in full. It is not normal to use this solution if the debts are for less than &pound;15,000. It is a useful tool as it avoids bankruptcy and protects personal assets.</span></p>','2010-12-17 16:43:05','2011-03-30 11:08:07','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Your&nbsp;relationship&nbsp;may have&nbsp;suffered</p>\r\n<p>Do you want to know what your options are?</p>','95_iStock_000010171389XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',97267,'2011-03-30 11:08:07','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','IndividualVoluntaryArrangements.jpg','image/jpeg',46005,'2011-01-13 14:40:44','Individual Voluntary Arrangements','','','Individual Voluntary Arrangements','/page/divorce-and-separation','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(109,'Accreditations','accreditations','Accreditations',109,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p>Many of our&nbsp;advisors have qualifications which&nbsp;illustrate specific expertise in their field and&nbsp;provides reassurance that they will always give you the best and most up to date advice.</p>\r\n<p>We have members of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Solicitors Regulatory Authority Childrens Panel</li>\r\n<li>Solicitors Regulatory Authority Family Panel</li>\r\n<li>Apil (Association of Personal Injury Lawyers)</li>\r\n<li>Resolution</li>\r\n<li>Collaborative Law</li>\r\n<li>STEP</li>\r\n<li>Solicitors for the Elderly</li>\r\n<li>Institution of Commercial &amp; Business Agents</li>\r\n<li>Corporate members of ICFIB (International Centre for Families In Business)</li>\r\n<li>Law Society Risk and Compliance Service</li>\r\n<li>Executive committee of the Law Management Section\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>','2011-01-17 12:25:31','2011-03-14 16:46:04','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(111,'Employment Law','employment_law_business','Employment law for employers',111,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>Keep on track</h2>\r\n<p>Employment law is ever changing and the biggest piece of advice we would give as an employer of staff is to keep up to date with it. Whether you are starting a business, running a business or exiting, if you have employed staff then it is crucial to get the right advice and we can guide you through the basics to get you up and running.</p>\r\n<p>We can advise you on:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contracts, including confidentiality clauses and restrictive covenants</li>\r\n<li>Disciplinary procedures</li>\r\n<li>How to handle dismissals and redundancies properly</li>\r\n<li>Maternity and paternity rights for your staff</li>\r\n<li>Discrimination law and Grievance procedures </li>\r\n<li>What to do if you end up in a Tribunal court hearing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We would always recommend an annual employment health check which will ensure your contracts are all up to date and worth the paper they are written on.&nbsp; Employers often believe their staff contracts are watertight but in reality often they are not due to more recent changes in the Law. If in doubt please check with our employment expert.</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lawdonut.co.uk/law/employment-law/?s=BAN082\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n<p>For more information on employment law please click here</p>\r\n</a><img src=\"../../..//assets/page_contents/111/contained_images/e302f95e9d90_153_The-Law-Donut.jpg?1326295165\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"0\" width=\"222\" height=\"62\" />','2011-01-21 12:01:24','2012-01-20 12:04:57','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Want a&nbsp;FREE employment healthcheck?</p>\r\n<p>Give your business some TLC</p>','tlc.JPG','image/pjpeg',18280,'2011-03-04 10:46:00','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','EmploymentLaw.jpg','image/jpeg',46536,'2011-01-21 12:02:10','Employment Law','','','Employment Law','/page/total-legal-care-insurance','',4,'family_highlight','','/page/total-legal-care-insurance','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(112,'Commercial Property','commercial_property_exiting','Selling a Business',112,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Whether you&nbsp;need to sell your business property or end your commerical lease&nbsp;our experienced team will get to know your business ensuring that our advice is tailored to your individual needs. There will often be things to consider that you may not have even thought about and&nbsp;we will talk you through your options step by step.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;We can help you with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The sale and purchase of offices and retail outlets</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Acquisition requirements such as finding and funding larger business premises </li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The disposal of your business and it&rsquo;s property</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The development and/or disposal of plots</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"../../../page/landlord-or-tenant-disputes\">Landlord and tenant issues</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Granting of leases</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tenancy agreements</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Green Leases</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Contested leases.&nbsp; Our commercial dispute resolution team can advise on other contentious issues arising out of commercial property</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Buying and selling commercial <a href=\"../../../page/property-abroad\">property abroad</a></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Notary Services</li>\r\n</ul>','2011-01-21 12:06:17','2011-11-29 14:52:58','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Family circumstances changing?</p>\r\n<p>Review your Will now</p>','58_iStock_000000753188XSmall.jpg','image/jpeg',144736,'2011-03-30 11:17:42','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','CommercialProperty.jpg','image/jpeg',57429,'2011-01-21 12:08:54','Commercial Property','','','Commercial Property','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(113,'Employment Law','employment_law_exiting','Employment Law',113,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Facing redundancies?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Employment law is ever changing and the biggest piece of advice we would give as an employer of staff is to keep up to date with it. If you are exiting your business you may have the difficult task of making staff redundant.&nbsp; If this is the case then we can help you ensure that you are following the correct procedures.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can also advise you on:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<li>Contracts, including confidentiality clauses and restrictive covenants</li>\r\n<li>Disciplinary procedures</li>\r\n<li>How to handle dismissals and redundancies properly</li>\r\n<li>Maternity and paternity rights for your staff</li>\r\n<li>Discrimination law and Grievance procedures </li>\r\n<li>What to do if you end up in a Tribunal court hearing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We would always recommend an annual employment health check which will ensure your contracts are all up to date and worth the paper they are written on.&nbsp; Employers often believe their staff contracts are watertight but in reality often they are not due to more recent changes in the Law. If in doubt please check with our employment expert.</p>','2011-01-21 12:12:48','2011-11-29 14:52:35','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>For ongoing employment advice at an affordable fixed monthly cost talk to us today about TLC</p>','110_tlc.JPG','image/jpeg',18257,'2011-03-30 11:20:59','','business_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','EmploymentLaw.jpg','image/jpeg',46536,'2011-01-21 12:13:40','Employment Law','','','Employment Law','/page/total-legal-care-insurance','',4,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(114,'Lasting Power of Attorney','lasting_power_of_attorney_elderly_services','Lasting Power of Attorney',114,0,0,1,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There may be a variety of reasons why you might need to look after someone else&rsquo;s affairs and there are several ways of ensuring that you are acting properly on their behalf.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A Lasting Power of Attorney (or LPA) is created to allow someone else the ability to look after your affairs if your mental capacity is lost. More often than not people create Lasting Powers of Attorney in later life when there is a higher chance of mental capacity being lost through dementia for example.&nbsp; However, mental capacity can be lost at any age as a result of say, an accident so we would also advise anyone with complex financial affairs to have one as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At Banner Jones we can advise you on the best course of action for your particular circumstances.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">One of our most frequent questions would be:</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">My father is elderly and has said that he would prefer me to deal with his bills and finances for him. Can I do this?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As long as your father has mental capacity he could do this by giving you &ldquo;power of attorney&rdquo; which will allow you to look after things for up to a year for him. If he later loses mental capacity, however, then the power of attorney will come to an end.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Alternatively, your father could give you Lasting Power of Attorney (LPA). This would not come to an end if your father were to lose mental capacity later on, and will last indefinitely, not just for one year. We would need to see your father personally so we can explain the LPA to him and make sure this is what he wants. We would then be able to prepare a document for him to sign, which would give you power to deal with his finances on his behalf.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will tailor-make the LPA to suit your father&rsquo;s wishes and we can discuss his options with him at the initial appointment. It cannot be used until it is registered with the Office of the Public Guardian, and we would be happy to deal with this too.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">What do I do next?</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are always keen to find the best solution possible for your particular circumstances, and we know that no two families are the same. Whatever your circumstances you can telephone us or make an appointment to discuss your situation with us in more detail. We will then be able advise you as to the best way forward.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Why not read our <a href=\"../../../assets/stored_documents/original/13_Factsheet - Lasting Power of Attorney.docx?1322579386\" target=\"_blank\">FREE GUIDE</a> to LPA\'s?</p>','2011-01-21 13:08:20','2011-11-29 15:34:54','','',1,2,0,NULL,1,0,'<p>Making a Will is a good place to start when planning for your future</p>\r\n<p>Make a Will today</p>','wom with baby.JPG','image/pjpeg',191221,'2011-03-01 12:21:06','','family_highlight',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','LastingPowerOfAttorney.jpg','image/jpeg',52253,'2011-01-21 13:10:35','Lasting Power of Attorney','','','Lasting Power of Attorney','/page/making-a-will','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(115,'<span class=\"family\">Services for <span>you & your family</span></span>','services_for_you_and_your_family','Services for you & your family',21,0,0,0,'2010-04-29 08:55:42','<h2>We\'re with you every step of the way&hellip;</h2>\r\n<p>You may never know when you are going to need the services of a solicitor, but one thing is for sure, you will need one at some point if your life. Whatever the matter let us worry about the legal jargon; you just sit back and relax in the knowledge that your case is safe in our hands.</p>\r\n<p>At Banner Jones we are here to help and guide you through all of life&rsquo;s little challenges and we&rsquo;re committed to being with you every step of the way.</p>\r\n<p>Through the good times...</p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullet_black_button\">\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/residential-property\">Moving House?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/pre-or-postmarital-partnership-agreements\">Getting Married?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/wills\">Had a baby?</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>And the bad...</p>\r\n<ul class=\"bullet_black_button\">\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/personal-injury\">Had an accident?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/probate\">Lost a loved one?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"../../../page/divorce-and-separation\">Relationship breaking down?</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Instructing a solicitor can often be a daunting task especially when you sometimes have no idea how much it will cost you. With the Banner Jones Fixed Fee promise you can be reassured that wherever possible you will know exactly what you are going 